{"term":"1956","caseName":"Government & Civic Employees Organizing Committee v. Windsor","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1956/423","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - April 29, 1957","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/13168","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 423, Government and Civic Employees Organizing Committee, CIO, an Unincorporated Association, et al., Appellants, versus S. F. Windsor et al.","start":0,"stop":15.895,"duration":15.9},{"text":"Mr. Shadur.","start":15.895,"stop":27.638,"duration":11.74}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.","start":27.638,"stop":32.817,"duration":5.18},{"text":"This case is an appeal from a judgment of the three-judge District Court for the Northern District of Alabama, Southern Division.","start":32.817,"stop":42.246,"duration":9.43},{"text":"That Court refused to enjoin the enforcement of the Alabama Solomon Act against the attack of the appellants here, claiming that that Act violated the Fourteenth Amendment.","start":42.246,"stop":56.5,"duration":14.25},{"text":"Now, that Act is set out at pages 2 and 3 of our brief.","start":56.5,"stop":61.762,"duration":5.26},{"text":"And with the Court's indulgence, I would like to call attention to its most relevant provisions which began with the first section.","start":61.762,"stop":70.15,"duration":8.39},{"text":"The first section defines a labor union --","start":70.15,"stop":72.362,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that to be found, please?","start":72.362,"stop":73.803,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Pardon?","start":73.803,"stop":74.238,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is it --","start":74.238,"stop":74.35,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"At pages 2 and 3 of our brief --","start":74.35,"stop":76.966,"duration":2.62}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Of you brief?","start":76.966,"stop":77.665,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- for convenience.","start":77.665,"stop":79.444,"duration":1.78},{"text":"A labor organization is defined as any organization of any kind in which employees participate for the purpose of dealing with one or more employers concerning grievances, labor disputes, wages, rates of pay, hours of employment or conditions of work.","start":79.444,"stop":100.72,"duration":21.28},{"text":"Then, Section 1, goes on to define public employee briefly as any person who is compensated in whole or in part by the State or by any state agency.","start":100.72,"stop":112.65,"duration":11.93},{"text":"Now, Section 2, which is the key Section of this statute, provides very simply that any public employee who becomes or remains a member of a labor union or labor organization or who participates in that union automatically forfeits all employment rights, benefits, and privileges which he has as a public employee.","start":112.65,"stop":138.588,"duration":25.94},{"text":"Section 3, to which I'll refer a little later, specifically excludes from the operation of the Act, all teachers, all employees of the State Docks Board, those are people who work for the railroad which is owned and operated by the State, and that further excludes all city and county employees.","start":138.588,"stop":159.049,"duration":20.46},{"text":"Now, the issues in this case, as we have stated them, are whether consistently with the Fourteenth Amendment, a State can constitutionally bar a state employee.","start":159.049,"stop":169.886,"duration":10.84},{"text":"In this case, a man who is a retail liquor sales man in a state-owned and operated liquor store, from his job and any other public employment solely because he belongs to a labor union, whether the State can compel that employee in order to retain his employment to resign his membership in that organization because one of it's ultimate purposes is the attainment of collective bargaining relationships with Government, with the people with whom it deals when and only when the State permits such collective bargaining to be carried on.","start":169.886,"stop":212.476,"duration":42.59},{"text":"Whether the Fourteenth Amendment permits the exercise and protects the exercise by that state employee of his rights of voluntary association, his rights of free speech, when those rights are exercised through his membership in a labor union.","start":212.476,"stop":230.485,"duration":18.01},{"text":"And finally, if and only if all these questions are determined against us, whether the State can limit that prohibition so that it excludes that prohibition from city employees, county employees, employees who are already organized in the labor unions.","start":230.485,"stop":251.54,"duration":21.05},{"text":"Now, the defendants don't join issue with us on these issues.","start":251.54,"stop":255.752,"duration":4.21},{"text":"They contend that the very nature of this union is such that collective bargaining is an inherent purpose which it says, cannot be abandoned voluntarily except through certain technical procedures which it says have not been followed that a person who belongs to this union can't give the State of Alabama his undivided allegiance and that the State can prohibit membership in point of union in order to ensure that undivided allegiance.","start":255.752,"stop":287.252,"duration":31.5}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Shadur.","start":287.252,"stop":288.163,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir?","start":288.163,"stop":288.586,"duration":0.42}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Sorry to interrupt you very early, but I would be able to follow your argument and meet the argument of this case much more understandingly if you'd be good enough to answer one or two questions as they're not clear in the –-","start":288.586,"stop":299.833,"duration":11.25}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":299.833,"stop":302.293,"duration":2.46}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"As I understand the decree from which we are appealing in the light of the opinion of the District Court of Judge Reed's amended rules.","start":302.293,"stop":314.928,"duration":12.63},{"text":"It didn't go to the merits.","start":314.928,"stop":316.496,"duration":1.57},{"text":"It didn't go to the issues that you've just summarized at all, as I understand it.","start":316.496,"stop":321.583,"duration":5.09},{"text":"It adhered to the earlier decision which came here in which that Court held that it can't tell what the statute means until the state court has elucidated its quote and meaning that that which the Alabama Supreme Court decided in 262 Alabama, merely said that this is -- within the terms of the statute, but it didn't tell you what the term of the statute -- it didn't -- it's within the range of the statute, but it didn't tell you what the contents are that brings somebody within.","start":321.583,"stop":357.565,"duration":35.98},{"text":"Would you please tell me what all that means?","start":357.565,"stop":359.759,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, as I understand the --","start":359.759,"stop":361.599,"duration":1.84}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, what they say, is it premature they're still holding the case?","start":361.599,"stop":366.253,"duration":4.65},{"text":"You get a constructive statute, non-concept of state -- the Supreme Court of Alabama will so construe it that to take away any claim of unconstitutionality?","start":366.253,"stop":374.752,"duration":8.5}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, that's not the way I read the District Court opinions.","start":374.752,"stop":377.975,"duration":3.22},{"text":"The first time that the matter came before the District Court, it did not have the benefit of the judgment of the Supreme Court of Alabama.","start":377.975,"stop":386.043,"duration":8.07},{"text":"At that point, it withheld jurisdiction.","start":386.043,"stop":388.783,"duration":2.74},{"text":"Now, however, there has been a specific adjudication by the Supreme Court of Alabama, not as a matter -- not only as a matter of language, but a specific holding on the identical record which is before this Court which was incorporated by reference before the United States District Court.","start":388.783,"stop":406.613,"duration":17.83}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then, tell me what that sentence mean.","start":406.613,"stop":409.152,"duration":2.54},{"text":"After the federal reading and consideration of the final decree of the Circuit Court of Montgomery County in equity and of the opinion of the Supreme Court of Alabama, here before mentioned, it is clear to us that the Alabama Court says not construed but the -- the Solomon has entered in such a manner as the arraignment on constitutional.","start":409.152,"stop":428.419,"duration":19.27},{"text":"Of course, we cannot assume that the state court will ever so construe such statute.","start":428.419,"stop":432.977,"duration":4.56},{"text":"What does that mean?","start":432.977,"stop":433.876,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"As I read that, Your Honor, that's simply saying that we have seen and read the application of the Solomon Act to these people, the plaintiffs in this case.","start":433.876,"stop":444.266,"duration":10.39},{"text":"But so reading that application, we do not find that to be an unconstitutional application.","start":444.266,"stop":448.904,"duration":4.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, what has the Alabama Supreme Court said the statute means?","start":448.904,"stop":451.85,"duration":2.95}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"The Alabama Supreme Court has said and its judgment is what speaks for the Alabama Supreme Court.","start":451.85,"stop":458.263,"duration":6.41},{"text":"It has a firm, a judgment below of the Circuit Court of Montgomery County which held that plaintiff union, its activities and its members all as described in the complaint are subject to the provisions of the Solomon Act.","start":458.263,"stop":476.48,"duration":18.22}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But does that tell me what the provisions of Solomon Act are as construable by a court?","start":476.48,"stop":481.764,"duration":5.28}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":481.764,"stop":482.425,"duration":0.66},{"text":"It's near --","start":482.425,"stop":482.644,"duration":0.22}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"About this morning, any instance and if you couldn't tell from a statute what it means, you have to get the court to tell you.","start":482.644,"stop":487.593,"duration":4.95}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But we now know, You Honor, exactly what the statute means because we can't --","start":487.593,"stop":490.579,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then, you don't know more than I do, known outside where the Alabama Supreme Court opinion.","start":490.579,"stop":494.67,"duration":4.09}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I agree that the Alabama Supreme Court opinion does not tell us, but the Alabama Supreme Court judgment does and it's the judgment –-","start":494.67,"stop":501.913,"duration":7.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that judgment?","start":501.913,"stop":502.23,"duration":0.32}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- which is determinative here.","start":502.23,"stop":503.784,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that?","start":503.784,"stop":503.993,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"The judgment is a judgment of affirmance.","start":503.993,"stop":527.218,"duration":23.22}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the one on page 30 of your --","start":527.218,"stop":528.768,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"At page --","start":528.768,"stop":530.23,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Beginning on page 30 of the Appendix B of your statement of jurisdiction?","start":530.23,"stop":534.328,"duration":4.1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, that thing -- (Inaudible)","start":534.328,"stop":538.975,"duration":4.65},{"text":"That -- Mr. Shadur says it doesn't tell us what the statute means.","start":538.975,"stop":542.959,"duration":3.98}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"In that paragraph --","start":542.959,"stop":547.094,"duration":4.14}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Of the Circuit Court judgment is on page 28 of your --","start":547.094,"stop":549.336,"duration":2.24}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Page 144, Your Honor.","start":549.336,"stop":551.665,"duration":2.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Of the record?","start":551.665,"stop":552.662,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Of the record.","start":552.662,"stop":554.12,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"144.","start":554.12,"stop":556.81,"duration":2.69}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"It gives us the judgment of the Circuit Court of Montgomery County.","start":556.81,"stop":562.086,"duration":5.28},{"text":"That's a judgment, which in the second paragraph, after holding that the Court had jurisdiction.","start":562.086,"stop":568.881,"duration":6.79},{"text":"States and holds that the statute of Alabama applies to complainant.","start":568.881,"stop":573.704,"duration":4.82},{"text":"That's the plaintiff union in this case, its activities and its members all as described in the complaint.","start":573.704,"stop":581.993,"duration":8.29},{"text":"We have then a fact situation which has been presented to the Court.","start":581.993,"stop":586.343,"duration":4.35},{"text":"The Court makes a ruling that under that fact situation, this organization is a union, a labor union, a labor organization within the meaning of that statute.","start":586.343,"stop":597.988,"duration":11.65},{"text":"The case then comes to the Supreme Court of Alabama and the Supreme Court of Alabama affirms that judgment.","start":597.988,"stop":605.005,"duration":7.02},{"text":"And that, Your Honor, is -- what we say is the binding application of the Solomon Act to our party here.","start":605.005,"stop":613.909,"duration":8.9}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that, but I still don't know what it is that you're forbidden or not forbidden that you're required to do or required not to do under the Solomon Act.","start":613.909,"stop":625.418,"duration":11.51},{"text":"And if the strange thing to have neither the Supreme Court of Alabama tell me that nor the District Court in which Judge Reed is a senior member.","start":625.418,"stop":632.737,"duration":7.32}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, there is one thing that is clear, the complex of activities that this plaintiff union has engaged in as described in the complaint and as found in the record is in fact prohibited by the Solomon Act because that's an authoritative construction by the Alabama courts.","start":632.737,"stop":649.399,"duration":16.66}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, that's an awful -- awful vacation undefined, for me, undefined scope of an injunction.","start":649.399,"stop":656.531,"duration":7.13}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I can't tell you whether I had this organization done two things less.","start":656.531,"stop":661.803,"duration":5.27},{"text":"It might not had been subject to the Act, but the thing that is certain from this record is that the things which it did have been held subject to this Act and we say that an organization which has done these things cannot be an organization in which membership is prohibited for all state employees as has been done by the Solomon Act.","start":661.803,"stop":684.12,"duration":22.32}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And I tell from this record -- and I tell from this record what particular thing carved out from your activities if you cease to do would still be allowed in the Solomon Act and what -- be held by the Supreme Court of Alabama not to be within it?","start":684.12,"stop":700.663,"duration":16.54}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No judge, but that's not relevant, Your Honor.","start":700.663,"stop":702.789,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Therefore -- therefore, do I understand this then, that it's your burden to show that no single thing in that -- in your activity may be prohibited by the Alabama Legislature, is that right?","start":702.789,"stop":716.044,"duration":13.25}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":716.044,"stop":716.58,"duration":0.54},{"text":"I think that's correct.","start":716.58,"stop":717.144,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Your burden then is, you -- you say this means to you that everything that you set forth in your complaint seeking to enjoin the Act is not -- is non-enjoinable, because if something in it is enjoinable and that hasn't been carved out, non-concept but that's enjoinable, and therefore, your complaint is all good.","start":717.144,"stop":739.303,"duration":22.16},{"text":"I must state, it's a very -- it's a very obscure basis on which to enjoin the state Act.","start":739.303,"stop":745.863,"duration":6.56}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I agree, Your Honor that the --","start":745.863,"stop":746.763,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not talking about constitutional law.","start":746.763,"stop":748.236,"duration":1.47},{"text":"I'm talking about the respect due by a District Court in enjoining state legislation.","start":748.236,"stop":753.591,"duration":5.36},{"text":"And we know very well the law that brought about the three-judge court against the readiness of district judges to declare a state legislation unconstitutional.","start":753.591,"stop":761.181,"duration":7.59}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But Your Honor, we have a fixed application of the Act to our party, and that application is the thing which we say is unconstitutional here.","start":761.181,"stop":769.822,"duration":8.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But -- but you agree that you must say that nothing that you do, everything that you do must be -- cannot constitutionally be -- be touched by -- by the -- by Alabama, is that right?","start":769.822,"stop":782.153,"duration":12.33}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, that our activity must be -- as it is described in this complaint is constitutionally protected against the state action which the Fourteenth Amendment has been intended.","start":782.153,"stop":793.695,"duration":11.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Every item, every item.","start":793.695,"stop":794.252,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Every item as described in the complaint, yes, Your Honor.","start":794.252,"stop":796.96,"duration":2.71}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, we have --","start":796.96,"stop":797.129,"duration":0.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"So that --","start":797.129,"stop":797.674,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- two types of plaintiffs, one is the union and the other is the members, is that right?","start":797.674,"stop":801.738,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":801.738,"stop":802.285,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"So, you had that burden as respects to those two, each of the two.","start":802.285,"stop":805.88,"duration":3.6}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":805.88,"stop":806.883,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And while you're on that Supreme -- Supreme Court of Alabama on which there's nothing about pulling it constitutional and you -- you interpreted as in feasibly holding a constitutional for it is passed on constitutional question itself?","start":806.883,"stop":820.154,"duration":13.27}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your -- yes, Your Honor.","start":820.154,"stop":821.547,"duration":1.39},{"text":"That was in the argument to the Alabama Supreme Court.","start":821.547,"stop":825.784,"duration":4.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the – it's non-concept as Alabama and we know the -- the diversity of the state rulings as the implication of Justice Burton's question.","start":825.784,"stop":836.931,"duration":11.15},{"text":"When I read that Alabama Supreme Court opinion, I first thought that all they decided and I'm not still clear that it isn't all they decided.","start":836.931,"stop":844.302,"duration":7.37},{"text":"We, now telling you're within it.","start":844.302,"stop":846.594,"duration":2.29},{"text":"We're not called upon to tell you whether it's unconstitutional.","start":846.594,"stop":849.804,"duration":3.21}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what they said explicitly, that we tell you within it and said nothing about the constitutionality.","start":849.804,"stop":853.699,"duration":3.89}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":853.699,"stop":854.244,"duration":0.55},{"text":"That's correct.","start":854.244,"stop":854.76,"duration":0.52},{"text":"The sole -- the sole effect of the judgment was to state that this organization, its activities, its members as described in the complaint is a labor union within the meaning of the Solomon Act and people who belonged to this organization are subject to all the penalties of the Solomon Act.","start":854.76,"stop":872.918,"duration":18.16}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And it can't be subject that it's constitutional?","start":872.918,"stop":875.372,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- that must necessarily follow and that's why we're here today, Your Honor.","start":875.372,"stop":878.911,"duration":3.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't see they necessarily follows.","start":878.911,"stop":881.579,"duration":2.67},{"text":"It's maybe merely a declaration that you're within it.","start":881.579,"stop":884.406,"duration":2.83}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, isn't that all you sought, sir?","start":884.406,"stop":886.91,"duration":2.5},{"text":"It wasn't your action one for an injunction upon the ground that you were not involved, a labor union or a labor organization within the meaning of the Solomon Act.","start":886.91,"stop":896.264,"duration":9.35}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, Your Honor.","start":896.264,"stop":897.819,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, they simply determine that you were a labor union or a labor organization within the meaning of the Solomon Act.","start":897.819,"stop":907.875,"duration":10.06}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":907.875,"stop":908.289,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"That's -- that's the some total of it, isn't it?","start":908.289,"stop":911.697,"duration":3.41}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":911.697,"stop":912.704,"duration":1.01}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, but that's an abstract declaration.","start":912.704,"stop":915.478,"duration":2.77}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But it's not an abstract declaration, Your Honor, because it's a declaration with respect to facts which are in the record.","start":915.478,"stop":921.655,"duration":6.18},{"text":"It is not a hypothetical case.","start":921.655,"stop":923.552,"duration":1.9},{"text":"It is a case dealing with facts.","start":923.552,"stop":924.721,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You said it's hypothetical, abstract is something else again.","start":924.721,"stop":930.228,"duration":5.51},{"text":"I mean by that, they merely say, \"We now tell you, you're within the term of the Act.\"","start":930.228,"stop":935.498,"duration":5.27},{"text":"But whether you -- whether you want to contest it, whether you are subject to the penalty, is that another story and come again if you want us to pass on that.","start":935.498,"stop":945.509,"duration":10.01}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":945.509,"stop":945.672,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The state court might do that if it wanted or couldn't it?","start":945.672,"stop":949.47,"duration":3.8},{"text":"That was (Voice Overlap) --","start":949.47,"stop":949.519,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, because the judgment not only went to the -- being subject to the Act, but in the opinion itself.","start":949.519,"stop":957.324,"duration":7.8},{"text":"The Court stated that there is no question that a person who is a member of this organization is subject to the penalties of the Solomon Act.","start":957.324,"stop":968.995,"duration":11.67}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they gave you notice.","start":968.995,"stop":971.697,"duration":2.7},{"text":"What are the penalties?","start":971.697,"stop":972.507,"duration":0.81},{"text":"Are they penal?","start":972.507,"stop":973.573,"duration":1.07}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"The penalties of the Solomon Act that's served -- stated or -- are the forfeiter --","start":973.573,"stop":977.014,"duration":3.44}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Any penal provisions?","start":977.014,"stop":978.493,"duration":1.48},{"text":"Any penal --","start":978.493,"stop":979.061,"duration":0.57}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, lost of employment, lost of all employment rights","start":979.061,"stop":981.447,"duration":2.39}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Am I wrong in recalling and -- and they will be.","start":981.447,"stop":984.155,"duration":2.71},{"text":"Isn't Alabama one of the States that does give advisory opinions?","start":984.155,"stop":988.277,"duration":4.12},{"text":"I -– not --","start":988.277,"stop":989.216,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not --","start":989.216,"stop":989.525,"duration":0.31}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the constitution","start":989.525,"stop":989.974,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry --","start":989.974,"stop":990.271,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- but they can't be.","start":990.271,"stop":990.595,"duration":0.32}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- I can't answer that question, Your Honor.","start":990.595,"stop":992.149,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I think --","start":992.149,"stop":992.375,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know.","start":992.375,"stop":994.035,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- well, it's a very -- I tell you at the outset, my prejudice, my personal -- not prejudice but bias against declaring a state Act unconstitutional on such a speculative and argumentative record.","start":994.035,"stop":1007.711,"duration":13.68},{"text":"I'm not saying you can't deal with my advice.","start":1007.711,"stop":1010.242,"duration":2.53},{"text":"I'll just say that I call it a bias out of deference.","start":1010.242,"stop":1013.214,"duration":2.97},{"text":"I think the good sound principle not to knock out state legislation revenue.","start":1013.214,"stop":1018.593,"duration":5.38}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Let me see if I can deal with that bias for a moment and see exactly what these activities are which were involved in the -- in the record that was before the Alabama Court and on which have nevertheless held that the Solomon Act apply.","start":1018.593,"stop":1035.369,"duration":16.78},{"text":"Before the -- before the Solomon Act was passed, the plaintiff union had asked the authorities of Alabama for collective bargaining.","start":1035.369,"stop":1048.362,"duration":12.99},{"text":"And specifically, the administrators of the Alcoholic Beverage Control Board which I'll call the ABC Board.","start":1048.362,"stop":1057.514,"duration":9.15},{"text":"Now, that right was denied to them and when that denial was made, they, thereafter, exceeded to that denial, and they, thereafter, did not assert either a right to bargain collectively nor a right to strike.","start":1057.514,"stop":1072.752,"duration":15.24},{"text":"And I might say that that – their act ceding to do that was in accordance with the objects of this union.","start":1072.752,"stop":1079.016,"duration":6.26},{"text":"The objects of this union are stated and the one relevant here to increase the wages and to improve the conditions of employment of our members by legislation, negotiation or other legitimate means.","start":1079.016,"stop":1094.074,"duration":15.06},{"text":"In other words, at that point, the union became as described by the only witness on this subject basically a discussion group.","start":1094.074,"stop":1105.477,"duration":11.4},{"text":"I'll get to the other activities which have engaged in just a moment, but it proceeded to discuss with its members privately and at meetings, such things as federal social security legislation, public housing, economic and political issues, civil rights, political candidates.","start":1105.477,"stop":1122.671,"duration":17.19},{"text":"Now, defendants have stressed two items of activity which they claim are inconsistent with this characterization, a plaintiff union as a discussion group.","start":1122.671,"stop":1133.156,"duration":10.48},{"text":"The first item of activity is -- and these are conceded, there is no question about this.","start":1133.156,"stop":1137.936,"duration":4.78},{"text":"These are part of the record.","start":1137.936,"stop":1139.786,"duration":1.85},{"text":"Plaintiff union and its members discussed the pros and cons of prospective legislation to provide for collective bargaining for state employees, and they thought about sponsoring that legislation.","start":1139.786,"stop":1152.059,"duration":12.27},{"text":"Similarly, when the Solomon Act was proposed in the state legislature, plaintiff union and its members contacted their legislators to try to defeat that Bill.","start":1152.059,"stop":1162.384,"duration":10.33},{"text":"Now, the other item of activity that defendants urge is that prior to passage of the Solomon Act, a representative of plaintiff union as part of its practice of assisting its members in connection with their individual employment problems appeared before the Alabama Personnel Board with some of those members to help settle the grievances which had arisen.","start":1162.384,"stop":1185.475,"duration":23.09},{"text":"Now, promptly after passage of the Solomon Act, the defendant's predecessors sent copies to the Bill to all the liquor stores and stated that all the employees had to sign those to confirm the fact they had read the Act.","start":1185.475,"stop":1199.187,"duration":13.71},{"text":"Plaintiff (Inaudible) and all the other ABC Board employees did in fact initial the Act.","start":1199.187,"stop":1206.114,"duration":6.93},{"text":"Immediately after that, the -- as the witness -- only witness on this subject stated, “The membership simply evaporated from 250 to 300 members.","start":1206.114,"stop":1216.81,"duration":10.7},{"text":"The union went down to a point where plaintiff (Inaudible) and perhaps one other member remained.","start":1216.81,"stop":1223.683,"duration":6.87},{"text":"Plaintiff (Inaudible) stated that he remained a member because he believed that he had a right to be a member of this organization in the same manner that he had a right to belong to his church.","start":1223.683,"stop":1234.536,"duration":10.85},{"text":"Now then, we filed suit in the District Court to which Mr. Justice Frankfurter has referred asking injunctive relief against the enforcement of the Act.","start":1234.536,"stop":1245.262,"duration":10.73},{"text":"The Court at that time withheld the exercise of jurisdiction, it abstained.","start":1245.262,"stop":1250.404,"duration":5.14},{"text":"That abstention came before this Court and was affirmed by this Court.","start":1250.404,"stop":1255.982,"duration":5.58},{"text":"At that time, no construction of the statute had been obtained from the Alabama Courts.","start":1255.982,"stop":1262.103,"duration":6.12},{"text":"At that point, suit was filed in the -- in the Circuit Court of Montgomery County.","start":1262.103,"stop":1267.824,"duration":5.72},{"text":"The judgment in the Circuit Court was that the Act did apply to plaintiff union, its members and activities as I have described those activities.","start":1267.824,"stop":1278.503,"duration":10.68},{"text":"There are no other elements which are in the record describing plaintiff's activities, plaintiff union's activities as they have been held to be subject to the Solomon Act.","start":1278.503,"stop":1290.208,"duration":11.71}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry, I didn't hear you.","start":1290.208,"stop":1292.947,"duration":2.74},{"text":"I may have been not inattentive, but looking at something else, in dealing under to that sense.","start":1292.947,"stop":1299.198,"duration":6.25},{"text":"Did you state that this union was -- was organically related to the CIO?","start":1299.198,"stop":1307.434,"duration":8.24}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":1307.434,"stop":1308.029,"duration":0.6},{"text":"Originally, it was formed by the CIO as an organizing committee.","start":1308.029,"stop":1314.894,"duration":6.87},{"text":"An organizing committee is a step prior to the formation of an international union.","start":1314.894,"stop":1321.554,"duration":6.66},{"text":"And it has -- has been stated in the -- in one of the footnotes in our original brief, consequently to the merger between the CIO and the AFL.","start":1321.554,"stop":1335.147,"duration":13.59},{"text":"This union has merged with its AFL affiliated counterpart, but under the merger agreement, every member of this union becomes and remains a member of the merged union and all the rights also carry over so that the provisions are applicable to this Court.","start":1335.147,"stop":1351.955,"duration":16.81}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But in -- in the burden that is yours, you have to contend that this union merely because it is -- it has a -- a tie with as part of the merger of -- of the CIO union, but that's the difficulty that if you do everything so far as doing sponsoring them, it could do everything it's doing, provided it did it on its own.","start":1351.955,"stop":1379.889,"duration":27.93},{"text":"Is that in the case for all we know?","start":1379.889,"stop":1383.188,"duration":3.3},{"text":"For all we know, the Supreme Court of Alabama might say, \"You can carry on all the activities, but you can't carry it on affiliated with the AFL and CIO.”","start":1383.188,"stop":1393.675,"duration":10.49}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":1393.675,"stop":1394.2,"duration":0.53},{"text":"I don't believe that is in the case.","start":1394.2,"stop":1395.792,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, how do you know it isn't?","start":1395.792,"stop":1396.987,"duration":1.2},{"text":"How do I know it isn't?","start":1396.987,"stop":1397.103,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the -- there is --","start":1397.103,"stop":1398.637,"duration":1.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"How do I know it isn't?","start":1398.637,"stop":1399.276,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- there is a specific area of activity which has been held subject to the Solomon Act.","start":1399.276,"stop":1404.289,"duration":5.01},{"text":"I think that's --","start":1404.289,"stop":1404.763,"duration":0.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"In spite of -- the Supreme Court of Alabama refers to this time and for all I know, that's the difficulty in the eyes of the Supreme Court of Alabama.","start":1404.763,"stop":1413.979,"duration":9.22},{"text":"Needless to say, I'm not talking about myself.","start":1413.979,"stop":1416.87,"duration":2.89},{"text":"Do you think there might be -- for one -- for one person, for me, might there be a legal, a different legal question to outlaw these activities as such and to outlaw the collective doing of those activities as part of the AFL-CIO.","start":1416.87,"stop":1433.863,"duration":16.99},{"text":"Might there not be a legal difference?","start":1433.863,"stop":1435.357,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, each of the provisions of the CIO constitution to which they refer in the Alabama Supreme Court opinion as part of the complex of this activity which is subject to the Solomon Act is also part of the organization as it stands there.","start":1435.357,"stop":1454.786,"duration":19.43}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That is not the same thing though.","start":1454.786,"stop":1456.516,"duration":1.73},{"text":"It's one thing for me to do something on my own.","start":1456.516,"stop":1459.871,"duration":3.36},{"text":"It's another thing for me to do something, connects with somebody else.","start":1459.871,"stop":1464.047,"duration":4.18},{"text":"I'm not saying that's a valid distinction.","start":1464.047,"stop":1466.064,"duration":2.02},{"text":"All I'm saying, do I know on this record that that is in the sticking point with Supreme Court of Alabama?","start":1466.064,"stop":1473.033,"duration":6.97}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I think that --","start":1473.033,"stop":1473.156,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do I not -- am I not entitled to think that it might be the sticking point for it?","start":1473.156,"stop":1477.651,"duration":4.5}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor --","start":1477.651,"stop":1477.911,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's the same thinking of which you've had in their opinion.","start":1477.911,"stop":1480.1,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"The sticking point for the State of Alabama as far as this case is concerned is the entire area of activities that's involved.","start":1480.1,"stop":1486.903,"duration":6.8}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You have no -- I don't think you're justified in saying that.","start":1486.903,"stop":1490.305,"duration":3.4},{"text":"That's my point that I do not know on what ground the Alabama Supreme Court went.","start":1490.305,"stop":1495.647,"duration":5.34}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, but we must, as Your Honor has correctly pointed out, state that each one of these activities is -- is inherent in the holding.","start":1495.647,"stop":1505.344,"duration":9.7},{"text":"That we don't know whether one of these being subtracted would nevertheless result in our being held subject to the Act.","start":1505.344,"stop":1510.729,"duration":5.38}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't make myself clear.","start":1510.729,"stop":1512.638,"duration":1.91},{"text":"There are two things for me.","start":1512.638,"stop":1513.825,"duration":1.19},{"text":"One, the activity that people in Alabama engages.","start":1513.825,"stop":1518.927,"duration":5.1},{"text":"Two, the fact that they engage in -- engage in those activities as part of a nationwide, almost an international organization.","start":1518.927,"stop":1530.429,"duration":11.5}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, this organization continues to engage in those activities, still as part of a nationwide organization with the same purposes.","start":1530.429,"stop":1539.789,"duration":9.36},{"text":"I submit that the record that as before this Court is in no way changed by the fact that it is now part of an AFL-CIO rather than that it is a part of a CIO.","start":1539.789,"stop":1551.096,"duration":11.31}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll ask you one more question and I'll desist.","start":1551.096,"stop":1553.693,"duration":2.6},{"text":"Is it -- is it therefore my understanding that one is to pass, one -- that the issue before us is whether the State of Alabama may, while allowing membership, while allowing its employees in various branch of its government to organize in and of themselves may prohibit them from being part of the AFL-CIO organization?","start":1553.693,"stop":1578.369,"duration":24.68},{"text":"Is that the issue before me?","start":1578.369,"stop":1580.906,"duration":2.54}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, I don't think so.","start":1580.906,"stop":1582.377,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":1582.377,"stop":1583.317,"duration":0.94},{"text":"How do I know it isn't?","start":1583.317,"stop":1588.005,"duration":4.69},{"text":"Leave the opinion to the Supreme Court of Alabama.","start":1588.005,"stop":1590.475,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I have done so with some difficulty into some way.","start":1590.475,"stop":1594.009,"duration":3.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, you encourage me, because I have nothing to do with that.","start":1594.009,"stop":1598.849,"duration":4.84}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, I submit to the Court that the construction and by construction, I would probably better use the \"application\" that the application that has been made of the statute by the Alabama Supreme Court, an application which applies to this union and to its members as those activities are described in the complaint and which I have now described is an unconstitutional application.","start":1598.849,"stop":1630.166,"duration":31.32},{"text":"And I don't believe that it requires really a great deal of constitutional citation for that purpose because before and now, the cases to which we have referred in our brief, the Wieman case, the Slochower case, Adler, Garner.","start":1630.166,"stop":1646.051,"duration":15.88},{"text":"All those cases have involved a conflict between a state interest and an interest of the government employee.","start":1646.051,"stop":1656.516,"duration":10.47},{"text":"I submit, if it pleases the Court, that there is no legitimate state interest which is here involved being protected as a price for taking away the constitutional rights of these individuals.","start":1656.516,"stop":1674.462,"duration":17.95},{"text":"There is no reasonable relationship between the fact which is the only fact required for this disqualification for employment that is the fact of union membership.","start":1674.462,"stop":1689.122,"duration":14.66},{"text":"There is no reasonable relationship between the fact of union membership and unsuitability for public employment.","start":1689.122,"stop":1697.449,"duration":8.33},{"text":"And yet, the Solomon Act specifically states and the Court, I submit, has read it in fact literally that any public employee who is a member of this labor organization loses his rights of employment.","start":1697.449,"stop":1716.21,"duration":18.76},{"text":"And labor organization is defined not as an organization in which there is insistence on collective bargaining with the State of Alabama because that's not in this case nor is that an organization which insist on the right to strike because that's not in this case either.","start":1716.21,"stop":1734.758,"duration":18.55},{"text":"It is only an organization in which employees participate for the purpose of dealing with one or more employers concerning these elements.","start":1734.758,"stop":1744.646,"duration":9.89},{"text":"Now, there is no question, but that this organization, the Government and Civic Employees Organizing Committee does deal with one or more employers regarding these things because it is an organization that does not restrict its activities to the ABC Board and where those activities of negotiation and bargaining are permissible under state law, it does engage in them.","start":1744.646,"stop":1771.943,"duration":27.3},{"text":"But where those activities are not permissible as they were advised by the defendant's predecessors in this case, there was no insistence on that so that what we have is the bare activities which are described in this complaint, discussion, the sponsoring of legislation, the opposition to other legislation and the processing of individual grievances.","start":1771.943,"stop":1798.519,"duration":26.58},{"text":"Only those activities are involved in this case and those activities have been specifically held to subject this union and the employees who are members of this union to the penalties under the Solomon Act.","start":1798.519,"stop":1813.753,"duration":15.23},{"text":"I submit that the due process question in this case virtually answers itself.","start":1813.753,"stop":1821.24,"duration":7.49},{"text":"This cannot satisfy the terms of this Court's statements in the Slochower case, the Wieman case, which require that before there can be restrictions on government employment, those restrictions must be reasonable.","start":1821.24,"stop":1838.18,"duration":16.94},{"text":"They must not be arbitrary.","start":1838.18,"stop":1840.033,"duration":1.85},{"text":"They must bear a relationship to this valid state purposes sought to be obtained.","start":1840.033,"stop":1848.419,"duration":8.39},{"text":"Apparently, the defendants would equate the idea that a government -- that a person does not have a right, the constitutional right to be a government employee with the conclusion that a government employee does not have constitutional rights, but of course that is not the case.","start":1848.419,"stop":1870.224,"duration":21.8},{"text":"I think that -- perhaps the best characterization of the Alabama position with respect to the activities of this organization is found that they're -- at pages 16 and 17 of the appellees' brief in which they refer to the witnesses -- witness battle, the union organizers' testimony as to sponsoring legislation and say, “This testimony not only tends to show that the union is not a mere discussion group as claimed, but that the union and the state employee members thereof have engaged in sponsoring collective bargaining legislation for state employees and -- and have attempted to defeat legislation which prohibits collective bargaining.","start":1870.224,"stop":1918.796,"duration":48.57},{"text":"As individuals, the constitutional right is there, but as state employees, it is not.","start":1918.796,"stop":1925.006,"duration":6.21},{"text":"Such action is contrary to the declared public policy of the State of Alabama.","start":1925.006,"stop":1931.926,"duration":6.92},{"text":"I submit, Your Honors, that the third public policy of the State of Alabama cannot prevail over this Court's decisions with respect to the scope of due process protection.","start":1931.926,"stop":1943.176,"duration":11.25},{"text":"Now, what do defendants fallback on?","start":1943.176,"stop":1945.889,"duration":2.71},{"text":"They turned to cases and various State Board cases in which it has been held that policemen and firemen may be prohibited from engaging in union activity and indeed from unionization.","start":1945.889,"stop":1962.429,"duration":16.54},{"text":"But each one of those cases was rested specifically on the proposition that there are special problems, special semi-military problems which relates to policemen and firemen.","start":1962.429,"stop":1978.335,"duration":15.91},{"text":"They -- each one of them has rested on the proposition that the police and fire departments are in a class apart.","start":1978.335,"stop":1985.421,"duration":7.09},{"text":"Both are at times charged with the preservation of the public order and for men, of all reasons, they owe to the public their undivided allegiance.","start":1985.421,"stop":1993.943,"duration":8.52},{"text":"The power in the state of complete control is imperatively necessary if discipline is to be maintained.","start":1993.943,"stop":2001.555,"duration":7.61},{"text":"Now, even if those decisions are available, and that's a problem that will come before this Court in another case which is now pending on its document.","start":2001.555,"stop":2010.167,"duration":8.61},{"text":"That statute, those cases and the statutes and ordinances which relate there would not control this case because there you have the narrowly drawn statutes dealing with perhaps a permissible problem.","start":2010.167,"stop":2025.335,"duration":15.17},{"text":"But the same considerations of this public order, safety, unqualified discipline which apply to the policemen and firemen do not apply to permit the prohibition of union organization and participation among all state employee.","start":2025.335,"stop":2042.949,"duration":17.61},{"text":"Plaintiff (Inaudible) is certainly not in a class apart.","start":2042.949,"stop":2047.301,"duration":4.35},{"text":"He is a liquor store clerk.","start":2047.301,"stop":2049.387,"duration":2.09},{"text":"Indeed, the Solomon Act actually accepts from its application, these policemen and firemen as city and county employees indeed in anomalous result if the purpose of this Act, the purpose of a legislation is to ensure the undivided allegiance, the necessary maintenance of complete discipline.","start":2049.387,"stop":2073.436,"duration":24.05},{"text":"There is no question that public employment and private employment are different.","start":2073.436,"stop":2077.157,"duration":3.72},{"text":"Defendants urged that at length and we certainly agree, but what defendants fail to recognize, or perhaps refused to recognize, is that the basic difference between those two types of employment is what brings us into court today.","start":2077.157,"stop":2091.058,"duration":13.9},{"text":"That is that the public action, the public employer when he acts engages in state action which is subject to the requirements of the Fourteenth Amendment and the state action which is represented by the Solomon Act violates the Due Process Clause of that Amendment.","start":2091.058,"stop":2108.12,"duration":17.06},{"text":"I might refer just --","start":2108.12,"stop":2109.107,"duration":0.99}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Shadur, you --","start":2109.107,"stop":2109.997,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2109.997,"stop":2110.407,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- you mentioned that it was an anomalous situation that they would -- would prohibit the state employees and not city and county employees in joining such organization.","start":2110.407,"stop":2122.502,"duration":12.09},{"text":"Do you claim that it's more than an anomaly or did you --","start":2122.502,"stop":2125.648,"duration":3.15}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor, we claim that that -- that that and I was about to speak to that, that that in itself is an arbitrary discrimination which does two things.","start":2125.648,"stop":2137.679,"duration":12.03},{"text":"First, it breaches the Equal Protection Clause, because the -- the exclusion from themselves are arbitrary with respect to the coverage that are brought there.","start":2137.679,"stop":2149.91,"duration":12.23},{"text":"And secondly, I think it points up even more sharply the fact that the statute itself is discriminatory because in the absence of those exclusions, they might make an argument.","start":2149.91,"stop":2163.073,"duration":13.16},{"text":"I don't say that it is justified by this record and in fact, it is not, that the purpose of the statute is to guard against the attempt to fix terms and conditions of employment by collective bargaining, but --","start":2163.073,"stop":2176.074,"duration":13}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do we know -- do we know what the scope of autonomy or a home rule as the phrase runs gave in Alabama City and county?","start":2176.074,"stop":2186.643,"duration":10.57},{"text":"You've indicated that the Docks Board has charged in railroad --","start":2186.643,"stop":2189.758,"duration":3.11}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2189.758,"stop":2190.155,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- owned by the State, restitute to that, is it?","start":2190.155,"stop":2193.875,"duration":3.72}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2193.875,"stop":2194.559,"duration":0.68},{"text":"That is --","start":2194.559,"stop":2194.587,"duration":0.03}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It was where --","start":2194.587,"stop":2195.112,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it's not restricted to that but the employees who are referred to here are the railroad employees, yes, Your Honors.","start":2195.112,"stop":2199.811,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) Are they subject to the Railway Labor Act?","start":2199.811,"stop":2201.779,"duration":1.97}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2201.779,"stop":2202.736,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Are they members of the brotherhood?","start":2202.736,"stop":2204.263,"duration":1.53}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"They are members of several Brotherhoods of railroad employees.","start":2204.263,"stop":2208.452,"duration":4.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And the classification relating as to that.","start":2208.452,"stop":2211.254,"duration":2.8},{"text":"Now, do we know -- how do I know what consideration has led the Alabama Legislature?","start":2211.254,"stop":2217.978,"duration":6.72},{"text":"I think there's a difference between employees of cities and counties as against state employees.","start":2217.978,"stop":2225.574,"duration":7.6}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I submit that no consideration can be conceived which would justify the -- the exclusion of the city and county employees and the inclusion of the state employees, for this reason.","start":2225.574,"stop":2241.023,"duration":15.45},{"text":"When you have is -- was the case before this Court in the McAdory case to which defendants refer, when you have a situation in which a State is regulating an area of activity.","start":2241.023,"stop":2254.237,"duration":13.21},{"text":"At that point, it may exclude an area of -- part of that area which it considers is already ampli-regulated and that was this Court's holding in McAdory.","start":2254.237,"stop":2266.202,"duration":11.97},{"text":"But when the form of the state legislation is to prohibit absolutely an area of activity than to engage in exclusions from that prohibition which have no relationship whatever to any legitimate state interest cannot possibly satisfy the Fourteenth Amendment.","start":2266.202,"stop":2285.824,"duration":19.62}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I know that cities or agencies of the State as subject to state constitutional provisions, a State can rearrange, do anything it pleases with its cities.","start":2285.824,"stop":2295.23,"duration":9.41},{"text":"But how do I know there isn't a scope of home rule that leads the legislature of Alabama to say, “We let Birmingham and Mobile take care of that, they have ample power.","start":2295.23,"stop":2305.885,"duration":10.66},{"text":"I'm sure in the cities that I know about, city employees are differentiated in all sorts of way from state employees.","start":2305.885,"stop":2312.388,"duration":6.5}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I -- the only distinction that exists here, because if you'll notice, the exclusions do not limit themselves, only to employees of cities or counties, they include the teachers, they include these employees of the state tax board.","start":2312.388,"stop":2326.73,"duration":14.34},{"text":"And the only --","start":2326.73,"stop":2327.01,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The teachers they might make a distinction again in the case of teachers and against others.","start":2327.01,"stop":2332.036,"duration":5.03}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But what are the distinctions as between them?","start":2332.036,"stop":2334.663,"duration":2.63},{"text":"Certainly, if there is any evil and neither defendants nor the state courts in the State of Alabama have ever articulated just what that evil is.","start":2334.663,"stop":2344.816,"duration":10.15},{"text":"But if there is any evil in the existence of union organization among state employees, how can it be said that that evil does not extend equally to these areas of completely arbitrary exclusion?","start":2344.816,"stop":2359.52,"duration":14.7},{"text":"There is one difference between them and that one difference is shown in Appendix A and that difference is that the people who are excluded are people who are already engaging in negotiation.","start":2359.52,"stop":2374.25,"duration":14.73},{"text":"Now, that, Your Honor, is certainly not a suitable distinction to excuse an exclusion from a prohibition against union organization to say, \"Well, these people are already within the area of evil.","start":2374.25,"stop":2389.955,"duration":15.7},{"text":"They're already engaging in collective bargaining.","start":2389.955,"stop":2392.544,"duration":2.59},{"text":"Therefore, we will exclude them from the provisions of an Act which prohibits collective bargaining and union organization among state employees.”","start":2392.544,"stop":2401.428,"duration":8.88}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It is a fact is it that they have unions in all of these -- all of these accepted employments?","start":2401.428,"stop":2408.059,"duration":6.63}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"There is nothing in the record with respect to teachers.","start":2408.059,"stop":2411.135,"duration":3.08},{"text":"There is in the record as plaintiff's exhibit 12 which we printed as Appendix A to our reply brief, specific affidavit covering the fact that since 1936, the Railroad Brotherhoods have negotiated schedules of wages and rules covering the employees of the State Dock -- Docks Board and further that there are municipal and county employees in Alabama who are members of labor organizations that negotiate their wages, hours and working conditions.","start":2411.135,"stop":2441.389,"duration":30.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Does it appear to -- with what international union, the local union who are affiliated in those domains?","start":2441.389,"stop":2448.832,"duration":7.44}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Only with respect to the State Docks Board employees that refers to the fact that they are affiliated with the Brotherhoods.","start":2448.832,"stop":2455.57,"duration":6.74}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that -- that rest on -- that may well rest on different situation, namely, that they're part of a railroad system with relationships with other railroad et cetera.","start":2455.57,"stop":2466.318,"duration":10.75}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But, Your Honor, that is not a matter of construction of the Act by the state court.","start":2466.318,"stop":2471.162,"duration":4.84},{"text":"That is a matter of a legislative exclusion and the legislative -- if the distinction between them had to do with the degree of affiliation with a union, an international union, then it would not be necessary to exclude them from the operation of the Act.","start":2471.162,"stop":2490.786,"duration":19.62},{"text":"That would take the course of the state determination by the Court as to what constitutes a labor organization if the total --","start":2490.786,"stop":2499.056,"duration":8.27}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But what if a legislate -- a legislature may say that railroad employees whether on government-owned railroads, or on privately-owned railroads present a different problem from -- from all other employees?","start":2499.056,"stop":2511.22,"duration":12.16}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But though, the --","start":2511.22,"stop":2512.012,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The legislation of the Commerce of United States has taking note of that fact.","start":2512.012,"stop":2515.015,"duration":3},{"text":"We've taken note of that fact.","start":2515.015,"stop":2516.288,"duration":1.27}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"But the legislature has not so said.","start":2516.288,"stop":2518.504,"duration":2.22},{"text":"The legislature has said that irrespective of -- with whom the employees of cities or counties, with whom the teachers, with whom the employees of the State Docks Board maybe affiliated, we will exclude them from the Act.","start":2518.504,"stop":2534.464,"duration":15.96}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And I'm suggesting that the teachers and the city and counties rest again on a differentiation of which the legislature again be might --","start":2534.464,"stop":2542.697,"duration":8.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose in your State Docks Board, you have -- you have employees who are -- are not affiliated with the Brotherhoods, haven't you?","start":2542.697,"stop":2551.716,"duration":9.02},{"text":"Perhaps you have a great plenty people working around the -- the docks for the maintenance of the docks, the buildings and so forth and -- and they're exempted, too, aren't they?","start":2551.716,"stop":2561.806,"duration":10.09}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2561.806,"stop":2562.581,"duration":0.78},{"text":"That's -- that only appears in the record from inference because the exhibit 12 to which I referred states that substantially all employees belong to these organizations.","start":2562.581,"stop":2573.548,"duration":10.97},{"text":"It said it is -- it is true that --","start":2573.548,"stop":2575.418,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"It's substantially all to the Brotherhood?","start":2575.418,"stop":2577.22,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"To the Brotherhood, but there are others which may belong to --","start":2577.22,"stop":2581.268,"duration":4.05}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What's the population of the Dock Board employees?","start":2581.268,"stop":2584.499,"duration":3.23},{"text":"About what –- what magnitude?","start":2584.499,"stop":2587.222,"duration":2.72}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know, Your Honor.","start":2587.222,"stop":2588.702,"duration":1.48},{"text":"I don't know.","start":2588.702,"stop":2589.539,"duration":0.84}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I didn't know that that Alabama also had a state-owned railroad.","start":2589.539,"stop":2593.012,"duration":3.47}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they seem to distinguish between the state-owned liquor stores and the state-owned railroads, whatever the basis for the distinction.","start":2593.012,"stop":2601.712,"duration":8.7},{"text":"I might advert before I close just very briefly to a -- an argument as to standing which was made by the appellees in the concluding portion of their brief.","start":2601.712,"stop":2616.738,"duration":15.03},{"text":"They state that the appellant union who does not have standing in this Court because this Court held in Hague against the CIO that only natural persons were entitled for the privileges and immunities that Section 1 of the Fourteenth Amendment secured for United States citizens.","start":2616.738,"stop":2635.131,"duration":18.39},{"text":"Of course, that has no application here.","start":2635.131,"stop":2638.084,"duration":2.95},{"text":"There is no question, although it may well be true that the labor organization is not a citizen for purposes of protection in the Privileges and Immunities Clause that it is most certainly a person within the meaning of the Equal Protection Clause and that is the Clause which we are invoking here.","start":2638.084,"stop":2659.006,"duration":20.92},{"text":"I submit, if it please the Court, that the Alabama Courts have construed the Solomon Act in the only matter in which the Court can ever construe an Act, that is by rendering a judgment on a specific record as to the applicability of that Act.","start":2659.006,"stop":2677.89,"duration":18.88},{"text":"On that specific record, it was held that the Solomon Act applies to this union and to the members of this union and their activities all as described in the complaint.","start":2677.89,"stop":2690.535,"duration":12.64},{"text":"That record is the identical record before this Court.","start":2690.535,"stop":2694.685,"duration":4.15},{"text":"I submit that there is no way in which it can be speculated as to the fact that on the record before this Court, the Alabama courts might hold otherwise because the Alabama courts have held specifically on this record that this union is subject to the Act.","start":2694.685,"stop":2711.903,"duration":17.22},{"text":"And under those circumstances, the constitutional question is squarely here and I submit there can only be one answer to that constitutional question.","start":2711.903,"stop":2721.504,"duration":9.6},{"text":"The Solomon Act, as it has been authoritatively applied by the Alabama Courts, violates the Fourteenth Amendment.","start":2721.504,"stop":2730.547,"duration":9.04}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Madison.","start":2730.547,"stop":2738.401,"duration":7.85}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"If Your Honor please, I'd like in a short time that remains to see if I can't -- to dispose of the argument that relates to any discrimination.","start":2738.401,"stop":2750.046,"duration":11.64},{"text":"When this case first went before the District Court for the first time, that Court took the position that the Act could be construed in a constitutional manner.","start":2750.046,"stop":2762.342,"duration":12.3},{"text":"It said it could have be construed as the prohibiting employees from belonging to the union for collective bargaining purposes.","start":2762.342,"stop":2771.949,"duration":9.61},{"text":"And then, it applied to doctrine of abstention which this Court later affirmed.","start":2771.949,"stop":2777.316,"duration":5.37},{"text":"Well, I don't think the Court would apply the doctrine of abstention to -- to say we are going to abstain to let the state court construe an unconstitutional statute.","start":2777.316,"stop":2789.328,"duration":12.01},{"text":"I think that is a determination in a sense that there is a constitutional way to apply the statute.","start":2789.328,"stop":2797.66,"duration":8.33},{"text":"So, that seems to me would get rid of the argument relative to being in any discrimination on faith of the Solomon Act.","start":2797.66,"stop":2808.771,"duration":11.11}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Can you satisfy the Supreme Court of Alabama to pass on constitutionality --","start":2808.771,"stop":2812.63,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir, not the Supreme Court of Alabama.","start":2812.63,"stop":2814.804,"duration":2.17},{"text":"I'm satisfied that -- that the District Court and this Court has -- has taken the position that it could be construed on a constitutional manner.","start":2814.804,"stop":2823.406,"duration":8.6},{"text":"They did not raise the question of constitutionality in the state court.","start":2823.406,"stop":2826.594,"duration":3.19}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, is it your position that the Supreme Court of Alabama has not passed on the question in the federal constitutionality with that?","start":2826.594,"stop":2832.13,"duration":5.54}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"They did not pass on the constitutionality.","start":2832.13,"stop":2834.152,"duration":2.02},{"text":"It was not raised in --","start":2834.152,"stop":2834.616,"duration":0.46}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"It was not ready for a federal court to pass something?","start":2834.616,"stop":2837.245,"duration":2.63}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, now, they'd probably like the federal court bend it in our state court so that way I can answer that too.","start":2837.245,"stop":2849.756,"duration":12.51},{"text":"As pointed out here, from some of the questions of -- from the bench, the legislative Alabama -- it prescribed the conditions of employment relative to immediate state agencies while cities, counties, school boards, the teachers there are the most agencies of the state.","start":2849.756,"stop":2870.936,"duration":21.18},{"text":"They're not to immediate agencies.","start":2870.936,"stop":2874.266,"duration":3.33},{"text":"And the legislature is leaving it to those different localities to determine for itself or themselves what they will do if anything with reference to public employees joined in labor union.","start":2874.266,"stop":2887.207,"duration":12.94},{"text":"Labor -- labor conditions in certain parts of State of Alabama and in certain cities and in certain areas may be one thing, and in other areas, it may be different.","start":2887.207,"stop":2896.454,"duration":9.25},{"text":"The labor relations may be fine in one area and it may be in certain respects if they would say that it would be objectionable to -- to cities and school system or the cities or the counties.","start":2896.454,"stop":2908.821,"duration":12.37},{"text":"And I think legislature had a right to -- to say, well, we will legislate this time, I guess with reference to the immediate state agencies which involved state employees.","start":2908.821,"stop":2918.591,"duration":9.77},{"text":"Now --","start":2918.591,"stop":2918.714,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Does it have the right -- does it have the right under your state constitution to regulate the conduct of employees in cities and counties?","start":2918.714,"stop":2930.784,"duration":12.07}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the legislature have the right?","start":2930.784,"stop":2931.813,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, yes.","start":2931.813,"stop":2932.677,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"I should say, sir, they'd have the same right with reference to them as they would with reference with the employees.","start":2932.677,"stop":2940.528,"duration":7.85}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"The same with teachers?","start":2940.528,"stop":2941.171,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2941.171,"stop":2941.707,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2941.707,"stop":2944.254,"duration":2.55}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, with reference to the -- the employees that are -- that belonged to the -- referred to as being employees of the State Docks, Section 3 of the Act, nor shall it apply to the those employees of the State Docks Board referred to in Title 38, Section 17, Court of Alabama 1940.","start":2944.254,"stop":2963.776,"duration":19.52},{"text":"Well, they are the railroad workers and it was thought that maybe the Railway Labor Act would have some application, maybe it had preempted the field and maybe legislature couldn't deal with those employees so it -- it left them out for that reason, that's why I think the legislature recognizes.","start":2963.776,"stop":2980.029,"duration":16.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why they'll leave the teachers out?","start":2980.029,"stop":2983.086,"duration":3.06}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"I should -- my -- my idea would be that they -- they left the teachers out to enable the local Board of Education to determine, whether or not in that judgment, they want to make any provisions to refer that the teachers belonged with the union.","start":2983.086,"stop":2995.569,"duration":12.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"How about the teachers in higher education, aren't they under the State?","start":2995.569,"stop":3000.145,"duration":4.58}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":3000.145,"stop":3000.497,"duration":0.35},{"text":"They get in a high educational system, the University of Alabama.","start":3000.497,"stop":3003.502,"duration":3.01},{"text":"I guess you might say they get a little closer to the --","start":3003.502,"stop":3005.494,"duration":1.99}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why would they -- why would they eliminate that one?","start":3005.494,"stop":3007.183,"duration":1.69}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I can't direct you why, Your Honor, but -- as why do they leave them out, but I guess I -- I wouldn't talk to them, I would answer that question.","start":3007.183,"stop":3014.409,"duration":7.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why would they leave out saying -- say policemen and -- and say firemen and county sheriffs and so forth?","start":3014.409,"stop":3021.531,"duration":7.12}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean --","start":3021.531,"stop":3024.229,"duration":2.7}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why would they leave them out when they -- when they took a -- a liquor sales?","start":3024.229,"stop":3030.347,"duration":6.12}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I want to -- the only the way that I can answer that question is that they leave it to the local unit to determine what they want to do with those people.","start":3030.347,"stop":3036.816,"duration":6.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, but my point is this, some of those are local and some of them were statewide.","start":3036.816,"stop":3041.164,"duration":4.35},{"text":"Now, is there anything to the argument of counsel to the effect that the legislature just said, \"Well, those that are argued, we're not going to fight with.","start":3041.164,"stop":3049.22,"duration":8.06},{"text":"We -- we'll let that be a fat accompli, but as to others, we're going to -- we're going to prohibit it.\"","start":3049.22,"stop":3055.905,"duration":6.69},{"text":"Is there anything to that argument?","start":3055.905,"stop":3061.553,"duration":5.65}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Because they –- they gave me a --","start":3061.553,"stop":3063.144,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, as I understood counsel, there were -- there were unions in the cities and in the counties among the employees.","start":3063.144,"stop":3071.287,"duration":8.14},{"text":"There were -- there were unions in the Docks, the State Docks employees.","start":3071.287,"stop":3078.8,"duration":7.51},{"text":"Now, did the legislature just say, as a matter of expediency, that we'll exempt all those who are organized but we will prevent those that are not organized from ever becoming organized, because that would bear on the question of whether it was a reasonable classification, I suppose.","start":3078.8,"stop":3096.248,"duration":17.45}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I don't think they did that.","start":3096.248,"stop":3098.543,"duration":2.3}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what -- the thing I can't understand is, what is -- why did they eliminate some of these people and the people in higher education?","start":3098.543,"stop":3108.682,"duration":10.14},{"text":"Why -- why wouldn't – why wouldn't they be just as amenable to it as a -- as a salesman in the state liquor store?","start":3108.682,"stop":3117.592,"duration":8.91}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, may I say Your Honor, it's improbably would be less likely to march back to force the liquor stores and it's unfair to organize labor, they might not insist on union, collecting the dues to check off I might say.","start":3117.592,"stop":3134.993,"duration":17.4},{"text":"There may be a number of reasons that I gave you as the legislation, I might say.","start":3134.993,"stop":3141.865,"duration":6.87}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll -- we'll recess now, Mr. Madison.","start":3141.865,"stop":3143.239,"duration":1.37}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":3143.239,"stop":3147.617,"duration":4.38}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - April 30, 1957","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/13309","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 423, Government and Civic Employees Organizing Committee, CIO, an Unincorporated Association, et --","start":0,"stop":11.734,"duration":11.73}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":11.734,"stop":15.525,"duration":3.79},{"text":"There isn't anything mystic or mysterious about the working to labor union.","start":15.525,"stop":21.63,"duration":6.1},{"text":"To put it generally known or how they operate in order to accomplish there objectives.","start":21.63,"stop":29.333,"duration":7.7},{"text":"As to general, all of them believe in the principle of collective-bargaining and they attempt to bring about collective-bargaining agreements.","start":29.333,"stop":37.034,"duration":7.7},{"text":"They use strike in such instances.","start":37.034,"stop":41.359,"duration":4.33},{"text":"Where union and non-union members become in daily contact, you'll find in sentence on paragraph 1 that should be close shop.","start":41.359,"stop":49.665,"duration":8.31}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Has Alabama experienced strikes in the case of Government employees, State employees?","start":49.665,"stop":54.32,"duration":4.66}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That is prohibited?","start":54.32,"stop":55.662,"duration":1.34}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":55.662,"stop":55.777,"duration":0.12},{"text":"Has it experience in strikes of -- by state employees?","start":55.777,"stop":61.056,"duration":5.28}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Insofar as I know only there may have been some threats.","start":61.056,"stop":67.037,"duration":5.98},{"text":"They do deal sometimes in picketing.","start":67.037,"stop":70.596,"duration":3.56},{"text":"Then we all know they have designed that this place to the stores, some other places unfair to organized labor.","start":70.596,"stop":80.717,"duration":10.12},{"text":"They insist sometimes on the collection of dues.","start":80.717,"stop":85.151,"duration":4.43},{"text":"They asked the employer to take out the money and remit.","start":85.151,"stop":90.735,"duration":5.58},{"text":"In their meeting they do have political discussions about candidates which they have a right to do, to a certain extent.","start":90.735,"stop":98.773,"duration":8.04},{"text":"And that they used to keep both on regular on (Inaudible) I'm not sure, United State Senate.","start":98.773,"stop":106.209,"duration":7.44},{"text":"We have under the merit system, political activity is prohibited.","start":106.209,"stop":111.777,"duration":5.57},{"text":"Here's where the borderline will come in these meetings.","start":111.777,"stop":114.132,"duration":2.36},{"text":"It's difficult to determine.","start":114.132,"stop":116.184,"duration":2.05},{"text":"Except that they have a right to say one will vote or against.","start":116.184,"stop":120.375,"duration":4.19},{"text":"You don't have the right to get into organization to make speeches and go out and engage in open political activities.","start":120.375,"stop":129.929,"duration":9.55},{"text":"Now, it seems to me that which one all of these things, that could be provided for by the State in its wisdom would be for the legislature to determine.","start":129.929,"stop":143.117,"duration":13.19},{"text":"Maybe some or all of them might constitutionally be prohibited by stand of state employee.","start":143.117,"stop":149.963,"duration":6.85},{"text":"They cannot belong to a union which engages in these activities.","start":149.963,"stop":154.619,"duration":4.66},{"text":"Certainly, that's true as to collective-bargaining.","start":154.619,"stop":159.171,"duration":4.55},{"text":"I don't know all the decisions of this Court.","start":159.171,"stop":161.294,"duration":2.12},{"text":"You can't read them all and you can't keep up with all them in all the state court decisions.","start":161.294,"stop":166.396,"duration":5.1},{"text":"But I believe this Court has said somewhere along the line that collective-bargaining has no place in public employment.","start":166.396,"stop":179.442,"duration":13.05},{"text":"Now, the District Court has said when this case was before it, contention was made that this Solomon Act which has been read to you all is unconstitutional on its face.","start":179.442,"stop":192.3,"duration":12.86},{"text":"Well, if there is any discrimination in this Act it appears on its page.","start":192.3,"stop":198.297,"duration":6},{"text":"The District Court said, we don't say there's no way to construe this Act in a constitutional manner.","start":198.297,"stop":208.039,"duration":9.74},{"text":"If it had been unconstitutional on its face for any reason, would there have been any logical reason for abstaining and sending the case back to the state court?","start":208.039,"stop":220.972,"duration":12.93},{"text":"Wouldn't if federal court have proceeded, is there no way other than to say it's unconstitutional, would have struck down right then.","start":220.972,"stop":230.004,"duration":9.03},{"text":"And when it came up here wouldn't this Court have said, “No.","start":230.004,"stop":234.306,"duration":4.3},{"text":"We are not going to affirm.","start":234.306,"stop":237.314,"duration":3.01},{"text":"There is no possible way it can be constitutional.","start":237.314,"stop":240.607,"duration":3.29},{"text":"So, why send it back?\"","start":240.607,"stop":242.997,"duration":2.39},{"text":"This Court didn't do this -- do that.","start":242.997,"stop":244.728,"duration":1.73},{"text":"It affirmed to stay in the lower court.","start":244.728,"stop":249.363,"duration":4.63},{"text":"Now, when the union -- and I'll make this point whether there's anything to it or not, I don't know what I'm going to mention.","start":249.363,"stop":256.596,"duration":7.23},{"text":"Up to that time, the -- the employee have seen and the union have been thriving together.","start":256.596,"stop":263.758,"duration":7.16},{"text":"But when they started in the in the Circuit Court of Montgomery County seeking a construction of this statute, the employee member was dropped or he didn't participate in the suit.And the union alone brought it.","start":263.758,"stop":278.411,"duration":14.65},{"text":"Why?","start":278.411,"stop":278.656,"duration":0.25},{"text":"I don't know.","start":278.656,"stop":279.593,"duration":0.94},{"text":"The other side may answer that (Inaudible) anyway.","start":279.593,"stop":284.674,"duration":5.08},{"text":"And then the issue was formulated there.","start":284.674,"stop":287.034,"duration":2.36},{"text":"It seems like it was studiously avoided to bring in any question about the constitutionality of Solomon Act.","start":287.034,"stop":294.782,"duration":7.75},{"text":"Now, we want you to tell us by declaratory judgment because we've got a dispute between us, as to whether or not you are a labor union or a labor organization within the meaning of the Solomon Act.","start":294.782,"stop":309.225,"duration":14.44}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Do I understand you to say that the question of constitutionality was studiously avoided (Inaudible)","start":309.225,"stop":313.502,"duration":4.28}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I said that -- yes.","start":313.502,"stop":314.742,"duration":1.24},{"text":"So, I'll put it this way.","start":314.742,"stop":315.758,"duration":1.02},{"text":"It was not raised.","start":315.758,"stop":317.069,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And in the Supreme Court likewise?","start":317.069,"stop":318.964,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"And in the Supreme Court likewise.","start":318.964,"stop":321.342,"duration":2.38}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And this was put in neither the lower state court nor the Supreme Court, the State has passed on the constitutional issue?","start":321.342,"stop":326.145,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, sir.","start":326.145,"stop":327.113,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you say it wasn't raised?","start":327.113,"stop":329.334,"duration":2.22}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"He wanted to know whether not he was a union within the meaning of the Solomon Act.","start":329.334,"stop":333.039,"duration":3.7}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes did you -- I think, did I hear you say correctly that the constitutionality of the Solomon Act, was not before your Supreme Court in the -- in the decision that was -- in which an -- an opinion was rendered in 262 Alabama?","start":333.039,"stop":350.131,"duration":17.09}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, sir.","start":350.131,"stop":351.443,"duration":1.31},{"text":"And it --","start":351.443,"stop":351.566,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":351.566,"stop":354.299,"duration":2.73}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"It was raised neither in the pleadings.","start":354.299,"stop":356.705,"duration":2.41},{"text":"It was argued before the Supreme Court on oral argument.","start":356.705,"stop":359.204,"duration":2.5},{"text":"The constitutional question was not involved.","start":359.204,"stop":361.777,"duration":2.57},{"text":"And it appears in the briefs, I believe.","start":361.777,"stop":363.954,"duration":2.18},{"text":"Now, those briefs were not made a part of this record.","start":363.954,"stop":366.17,"duration":2.22}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What appears in the briefs?","start":366.17,"stop":367.874,"duration":1.7}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That if there's no argument, of course, the constitutional question was argued.","start":367.874,"stop":371.262,"duration":3.39},{"text":"But each side stated, as I recall.","start":371.262,"stop":373.114,"duration":1.85},{"text":"There is no constitutional question involved in this case.","start":373.114,"stop":376.069,"duration":2.96},{"text":"Just whether or not (Voice Overlap) --","start":376.069,"stop":376.238,"duration":0.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Voice Overlap) -- That was in the brief that lead to the decision 262 Alabama?","start":376.238,"stop":382.712,"duration":6.47}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That was in the brief filed in this -- in this case.","start":382.712,"stop":384.653,"duration":1.94},{"text":"Is that correct?","start":384.653,"stop":387.63,"duration":2.98}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Can you supply us with a copy of that brief so we -- we may read it for ourselves?","start":387.63,"stop":396.147,"duration":8.52}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe they are in the Court record because they were introduced in evidence on the circuit trial before the District Court.","start":396.147,"stop":402.499,"duration":6.35},{"text":"And I think they were left out being printed, but I believe they are here in this Court now.","start":402.499,"stop":405.96,"duration":3.46}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, would you just state as accurately as you can what was stated in that -- in that brief to that effect?","start":405.96,"stop":413.874,"duration":7.91}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"In the brief?","start":413.874,"stop":415.21,"duration":1.34}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's what we're talking about isn't it?","start":415.21,"stop":416.963,"duration":1.75}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean in the state court brief, what was in it or what was left out?","start":416.963,"stop":420.287,"duration":3.32}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"On this -- on this particular subject that the -- that the constitutional question was not being raised.","start":420.287,"stop":426.363,"duration":6.08},{"text":"That's what I understood you to say as the brief showed --","start":426.363,"stop":428.534,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"It was -- it was argued in -- in substance in that case.","start":428.534,"stop":432.184,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon?","start":432.184,"stop":433.147,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That it was argued in substance.","start":433.147,"stop":434.619,"duration":1.47},{"text":"I'll state the substance as nearly as I can recall --","start":434.619,"stop":436.692,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":436.692,"stop":438.131,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"-- by the other side that they had attempted to bargain collectively with the A.B.C. Board.","start":438.131,"stop":449.244,"duration":11.11},{"text":"At the A.B.C. Board had refused to bargain with them and hence they had ceased any attempt to bargain collectively.","start":449.244,"stop":460.739,"duration":11.49},{"text":"They then said that we have from that time on conducted merely a discussion group.","start":460.739,"stop":472.476,"duration":11.74},{"text":"And being merely a discussion group, we say that the Solomon Act does not apply to us.","start":472.476,"stop":480.611,"duration":8.13},{"text":"And we ask this Court to hold that we are a union and our activities as such.","start":480.611,"stop":487.593,"duration":6.98},{"text":"That we do not come within the provisions of the Solomon Act.","start":487.593,"stop":493.244,"duration":5.65},{"text":"We argued on the other side.","start":493.244,"stop":494.482,"duration":1.24},{"text":"Do you want the other side too, Your Honor?","start":494.482,"stop":495.932,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Before you're going to the other side, let me have no doubt about what you're saying.","start":495.932,"stop":503.153,"duration":7.22},{"text":"Am I right in inferring from what you've just said that the others -- that the -- the present petitioners for the present appellants they don't appeal.","start":503.153,"stop":514.025,"duration":10.87},{"text":"But the present appellants in the -- in the argument in the proceedings before the Supreme Court of -- of Alabama claimed that there were a discussion group --","start":514.025,"stop":528.696,"duration":14.67}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":528.696,"stop":528.884,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and therefore, outside of the scope of the Solomon Act.","start":528.884,"stop":531.743,"duration":2.86}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":531.743,"stop":533.042,"duration":1.3}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that right?","start":533.042,"stop":533.561,"duration":0.52}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's my understanding there.","start":533.561,"stop":538.102,"duration":4.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And the Court -- and the Alabama's Supreme Court decided that they were not a discussion group merely --","start":538.102,"stop":544.471,"duration":6.37}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, sir.","start":544.471,"stop":544.66,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- but that they were brought, that their activities brought them within the terms of the Solomon Act and that's all it decided.","start":544.66,"stop":552.948,"duration":8.29}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":552.948,"stop":553.134,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that what you're saying?","start":553.134,"stop":554.033,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, sir.","start":554.033,"stop":555.085,"duration":1.05},{"text":"And I want to state that's the basis for the Supreme Court of Alabama decision.","start":555.085,"stop":558.109,"duration":3.02},{"text":"There should be no mistake between them.","start":558.109,"stop":559.628,"duration":1.52},{"text":"Let me get that clear.","start":559.628,"stop":562.249,"duration":2.62},{"text":"The Supreme Court of Alabama went into the rules of this organization, went into the Constitution.","start":562.249,"stop":569.427,"duration":7.18},{"text":"It went into the law of Mr. Philip Murray when it was setting up, this organization all of which provide for collective-bargaining and it's in -- one of the main purposes and objectives of the union.","start":569.427,"stop":580.014,"duration":10.59},{"text":"It went into the clauses whereby the -- the member should take an oath to abide by those rules and regulations.","start":580.014,"stop":586.92,"duration":6.91},{"text":"That then none of them can't be changed without approval by the executive committee.","start":586.92,"stop":591.539,"duration":4.62},{"text":"They went into the question that this union is connected with the International Union.","start":591.539,"stop":596.125,"duration":4.59},{"text":"And in that constitution of the International provided for collective-bargaining.","start":596.125,"stop":600.545,"duration":4.42},{"text":"And that those rules and regulations constitute a contract between a union and the members and between the members themselves.","start":600.545,"stop":609.429,"duration":8.88},{"text":"And it then went on to say that a local union merely on the whim of a representative or the local group cannot change the declared purposes and objectives of that national or international organization.","start":609.429,"stop":624.859,"duration":15.43},{"text":"And then they --","start":624.859,"stop":624.992,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":624.992,"stop":625.147,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"-- threw him some moreover things about that activities, which I will discuss.","start":625.147,"stop":628.979,"duration":3.83}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Madison, I haven't quite got an answer to -- to the question.","start":628.979,"stop":633.608,"duration":4.63},{"text":"I understood you to say that petitioner, in its brief in the state court and its argument represented to the Court that there was not a constitutional question involved.","start":633.608,"stop":646.736,"duration":13.13},{"text":"That it was only the question as to whether the ex-conduct of -- of the petitioner constituted or brought them in -- within the act itself.","start":646.736,"stop":660.179,"duration":13.44},{"text":"Now, is that -- I -- I just want to know if I'm correct in -- in my recollection of what you said?","start":660.179,"stop":665.877,"duration":5.7}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor I will put it this way because it -- it maybe important, you'll think.","start":665.877,"stop":669.978,"duration":4.1},{"text":"I don't want misstating it.","start":669.978,"stop":671.598,"duration":1.62},{"text":"My recollection is that it occurs in both briefs.","start":671.598,"stop":675.073,"duration":3.48},{"text":"I know it does in the brief filed on behalf of the State.","start":675.073,"stop":679.016,"duration":3.94},{"text":"What I know is that we did argue -- argue the constitutional question for fear that the Court might say this is of such public importance or something.You go ahead and deal with it anyhow.","start":679.016,"stop":688.11,"duration":9.09},{"text":"What we stated before we did that, we didn't think that question was in and had been raised.","start":688.11,"stop":692.327,"duration":4.22}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But you --","start":692.327,"stop":692.41,"duration":0.08}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"In my recollection is they did the same thing.","start":692.41,"stop":694.891,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You --","start":694.891,"stop":694.984,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"But I'd rather rely on these briefs.","start":694.984,"stop":696.567,"duration":1.58},{"text":"They're here and in order that you may determine for yourself just exactly what they did say.","start":696.567,"stop":701.456,"duration":4.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But you -- you went beyond that.","start":701.456,"stop":703.222,"duration":1.77},{"text":"You also said, if I understood you correctly, that the pleadings disclosed that the constitutional -- that there was no constitutional attack on the Solomon Act.","start":703.222,"stop":714.453,"duration":11.23}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- well, I -- it -- it doesn't it -- I'll put it this way.","start":714.453,"stop":717.438,"duration":2.99},{"text":"I'll put in the reverse.","start":717.438,"stop":719.181,"duration":1.74},{"text":"There's nothing mentioned in the pleadings that the Solomon Act is unconstitutional.","start":719.181,"stop":723.44,"duration":4.26}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":723.44,"stop":728.362,"duration":4.92},{"text":"What -- would you mind stating what is meant, what -- what proper inferences may be drawn from the judgment of the Montgomery County decree saying the prayer for injunctive relief is denied.","start":728.362,"stop":751.258,"duration":22.9},{"text":"But what's the significance of that?","start":751.258,"stop":754.948,"duration":3.69}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they asked that the -- the members of the A.B.C. Board and this manager of the store, the supervisor of all to be enjoined from enforcing the provisions of the Solomon Act.","start":754.948,"stop":769.176,"duration":14.23},{"text":"Now, they did that on a theory, I guess, if they thought they were not under it and A.B.C. Board was attempting to apply it to them, that you ought to be enjoined from that.","start":769.176,"stop":777.104,"duration":7.93}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And did the prayer, that's your remark a little earlier that the pleadings did not attack the constitutionality?","start":777.104,"stop":785.085,"duration":7.98},{"text":"That covers I take it, the terms of the prayer by the complainant before the Montgomery County Court?","start":785.085,"stop":790.693,"duration":5.61}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Our recollection is correct.","start":790.693,"stop":791.602,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But they did not say a wherefore (1) the Act is unconstitutional.","start":791.602,"stop":796.7,"duration":5.1},{"text":"Wherefore (2) proceedings under it or acts under it should be enjoined.","start":796.7,"stop":804.857,"duration":8.16},{"text":"As far as, my recollection am I wrong or right in -- in having an impression that in your State, you can, one can get an advice from somebody.","start":804.857,"stop":811.991,"duration":7.13},{"text":"The Governor or the legislature you can get an advice of the opinion?","start":811.991,"stop":814.93,"duration":2.94}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"The Governor can ask for an advice or opinion and so can members of the legislation but nobody else can.","start":814.93,"stop":819.245,"duration":4.32}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Nobody else.","start":819.245,"stop":820.159,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"And they don't have any force or effect of law.","start":820.159,"stop":821.803,"duration":1.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but as of the -- the Governor in the legislature.","start":821.803,"stop":824.338,"duration":2.53}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's all that I know of.","start":824.338,"stop":824.827,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But by statute --","start":824.827,"stop":825.682,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Though lots of them will try to get them with the admonition.","start":825.682,"stop":827.703,"duration":2.02}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that by statute or your constitution?","start":827.703,"stop":829.852,"duration":2.15}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"I'd -- I don't whether -- I don't recall whether it's constitution or the statute.","start":829.852,"stop":833.324,"duration":3.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":833.324,"stop":837.664,"duration":4.34}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, after -- after the Supreme Court had gone into these things that I pointed out, the constitution and rules of the -- this organization and -- and make that declaration for whatever they be aware.","start":837.664,"stop":850.165,"duration":12.5},{"text":"Now, that case then went back to the District Court for the second time that court had let it stand for a reasonable time.","start":850.165,"stop":861.622,"duration":11.46},{"text":"In order to enable the appellants and I point that isn't one of them that makes (Inaudible), showing the remedy, he might have in the state court.","start":861.622,"stop":871.73,"duration":10.11},{"text":"And then insisted in that court, that the District Court then pass on the constitutional issues which it raised when it first filed the suit.","start":871.73,"stop":883.764,"duration":12.03},{"text":"Then the three-judge District Court, we had a hearing and argument up there.","start":883.764,"stop":888.142,"duration":4.38},{"text":"We introduced the record that before the Supreme Court of Alabama, introduced the briefs on both sides.","start":888.142,"stop":897.686,"duration":9.54},{"text":"And then Judge Graves who was the presiding judge in that case along with Judge Grooms and Judge Lynn.","start":897.686,"stop":905.327,"duration":7.64},{"text":"They stated that they had given careful consideration to the decision of the lower court, that is the lower state court and the decision of the Supreme Court of Alabama and used the language, as I recall that they were clear to the conclusion that the state courts had not construed the Solomon Act in an unconstitutional manner.","start":905.327,"stop":928.704,"duration":23.38}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Excuse me.","start":928.704,"stop":929.268,"duration":0.56},{"text":"Can you please tell me what -- what's your understanding of this allegation of the complaint?","start":929.268,"stop":934.256,"duration":4.99},{"text":"I'm looking at page 77, tenth paragraph.","start":934.256,"stop":945.322,"duration":11.07},{"text":"Reads substantial civil and property rights are depended upon the determination of this controversy and the actions of respondent consisting of the said statue applies from plaintiff and its members and so forth.","start":945.322,"stop":960.693,"duration":15.37}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you -- you mean, Your Honor that you might sort of stretch that a little bit to get it cover the constitutional question?","start":960.693,"stop":966.717,"duration":6.02}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm asking you what it means as you understand it.","start":966.717,"stop":974.964,"duration":8.25}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Where does that appears, sir?","start":974.964,"stop":976.455,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"It appears in paragraph 10, the second sentence, substantial civil and property rights are depended upon et cetera.","start":976.455,"stop":996.606,"duration":20.15}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in short I think it means, Your Honor, that they've been losing $2 a month per person in dues.","start":996.606,"stop":1006.557,"duration":9.95},{"text":"And if you construe this, actually it was not to embrace them they'd be able to have those members participate for the collection of dues.","start":1006.557,"stop":1018.788,"duration":12.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What happens after the Alabama Supreme Court got through because of what they did in 262.","start":1018.788,"stop":1027.094,"duration":8.31},{"text":"Is that automatically does that go back to the Circuit Court of Montgomery County or automatically that's just an affirmance of the decree below?","start":1027.094,"stop":1034.955,"duration":7.86}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"It was an affirmance of the decree below.","start":1034.955,"stop":1036.635,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"How did you know (Voice Overlap)","start":1036.635,"stop":1037.448,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"They didn't file an application for rehearing.","start":1037.448,"stop":1039.513,"duration":2.06},{"text":"They didn't seek to have any determination and the further determination if one could be had and I don't whether it could be if not by this Court or what Supreme Court of Alabama.","start":1039.513,"stop":1046.557,"duration":7.04}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That is -- that is Montgomery -- what you say -- to see if this is correct, in your -- in your point of view.","start":1046.557,"stop":1054.297,"duration":7.74},{"text":"That the Montgomery -- the county court of Montgomery County or the Circuit Court of Montgomery County in effect had before it a prayer for a declaration whether this union or this organization is within the Act period.","start":1054.297,"stop":1073.342,"duration":19.05},{"text":"They said they were within the Act.","start":1073.342,"stop":1075.117,"duration":1.77},{"text":"So, therefore, they wouldn't enjoin.","start":1075.117,"stop":1077.187,"duration":2.07},{"text":"Then went up to Supreme Court, the Supreme Court said yes, you're within the Act period.","start":1077.187,"stop":1082.741,"duration":5.55},{"text":"And that's all.","start":1082.741,"stop":1083.397,"duration":0.66},{"text":"Is that right?","start":1083.397,"stop":1083.927,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":1083.927,"stop":1084.181,"duration":0.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's your view, of what took place in the Alabama court?","start":1084.181,"stop":1086.44,"duration":2.26}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, sir.","start":1086.44,"stop":1088.323,"duration":1.88}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And no more?","start":1088.323,"stop":1089.538,"duration":1.21}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"No more.","start":1089.538,"stop":1090.459,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I've thought your position was that the petition, Alabama court the second clause it says looking for the old picture.","start":1090.459,"stop":1102.268,"duration":11.81},{"text":"This (Inaudible)","start":1102.268,"stop":1111.964,"duration":9.7}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Well it did, Your Honor, but I think what -- what I meant was that's the same thing that he asked, if -- if I understand it correctly.","start":1111.964,"stop":1120.637,"duration":8.67},{"text":"I don't get the distinction between them.","start":1120.637,"stop":1123.326,"duration":2.69}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But did the Alabama Supreme Court say, you notice of Internal organization?","start":1123.326,"stop":1129.107,"duration":5.78}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":1129.107,"stop":1130.938,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I understand it, within the purview of Solomon Act.","start":1130.938,"stop":1133.565,"duration":2.63}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":1133.565,"stop":1133.933,"duration":0.37},{"text":"They did not say that.","start":1133.933,"stop":1134.923,"duration":0.99}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What did they say?","start":1134.923,"stop":1136.326,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"It said that you're not a discussion group.","start":1136.326,"stop":1138.712,"duration":2.39}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what I thought.","start":1138.712,"stop":1140.22,"duration":1.51}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And therefore, and therefore it was within the Act?","start":1140.22,"stop":1142.435,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right sir.","start":1142.435,"stop":1142.9,"duration":0.47}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"It forces within the Act.","start":1142.9,"stop":1144.228,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Period.","start":1144.228,"stop":1145.114,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Period.","start":1145.114,"stop":1146.988,"duration":1.87},{"text":"And they, they got my period in the wrong place.","start":1146.988,"stop":1148.835,"duration":1.85},{"text":"But I understand to be in the right place.","start":1148.835,"stop":1150.268,"duration":1.43}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that.","start":1150.268,"stop":1157.897,"duration":7.63}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, I do wish to deal just briefly in conclusion with this.","start":1157.897,"stop":1163.446,"duration":5.55},{"text":"As I said, that the courts have said, this Act could be construed on a constitutional manner.I think that means something.","start":1163.446,"stop":1169.291,"duration":5.85},{"text":"I think that take cares of some their argument about discrimination.","start":1169.291,"stop":1174.441,"duration":5.15},{"text":"But as I pointed out, that the labor relations in different parts of the State of Alabama, as if the different county Government body, the different city Government bodies and difference maybe among the teachers and the Board of Education.","start":1174.441,"stop":1189.742,"duration":15.3},{"text":"It may be necessary and desirable into some parts for the local communities to legislate by ordinance of resolutions or by rule or some other way.","start":1189.742,"stop":1199.934,"duration":10.19},{"text":"Either one way another on these questions.","start":1199.934,"stop":1205.223,"duration":5.29},{"text":"Now, yesterday, Mr. Chief Justice has been asking about the higher institutions of learning.","start":1205.223,"stop":1212.337,"duration":7.11}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1212.337,"stop":1213.998,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Over in the University of Alabama, are possibly our two largest.","start":1213.998,"stop":1218.903,"duration":4.9},{"text":"They are governed by Board of Trustees.","start":1218.903,"stop":1223.267,"duration":4.36},{"text":"And it -- the -- it is provided on their constitution that the sole management and control of those two institutions, shall vest in the Board of Trustees.","start":1223.267,"stop":1233.136,"duration":9.87},{"text":"Now, maybe the others are covered in the exemption containing the statute or that's are not covered by the Solomon Act, to -- to have Board of Trustees or some other civil board.","start":1233.136,"stop":1244.767,"duration":11.63},{"text":"They undoubtedly have rule-making power just exactly like of County Board of Education or City Board of Education.","start":1244.767,"stop":1252.107,"duration":7.34},{"text":"If they adopted the rules, the question would be as -- as I conceive it to be whether not that rule that they've adopted proscribing public employment, of course, of membership to the labor union whether or not that was a reasonable rule.","start":1252.107,"stop":1265.974,"duration":13.87},{"text":"I believe this Court have said that there is constitutional protection to a public employee against unreasonable arbitrary action.Now, with sum on all of these reasons I pointed out about the activities of -- of the labor union they maybe entirely in order -- entirely order permissible in private employment but not in public employment.","start":1265.974,"stop":1292.466,"duration":26.49}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What -- what percentage of your employees of your port authority that -- that's mentioned in here, along the brotherhoods?","start":1292.466,"stop":1302.83,"duration":10.36}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor that their game there maybe a dispute.","start":1302.83,"stop":1307.659,"duration":4.83},{"text":"It's not the purpose between counsels.","start":1307.659,"stop":1311.819,"duration":4.16},{"text":"It is my -- if my recollection of what that act provides and what our state statute said that all of them belong, because all of them are railway employees.","start":1311.819,"stop":1324.295,"duration":12.48},{"text":"Now, I understood him to say yesterday that there were some excluded who worked for the docks that were not railway employees.","start":1324.295,"stop":1331.952,"duration":7.66},{"text":"Now, it's marked in the section that that is a mistake that I think the one that excluded the whole railway employees.","start":1331.952,"stop":1340.747,"duration":8.8}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, does the Act say so?","start":1340.747,"stop":1342.013,"duration":1.27},{"text":"I don't (Voice Overlap) --","start":1342.013,"stop":1342.354,"duration":0.34}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"It refers to another Act in the code and that Act said so.","start":1342.354,"stop":1345.157,"duration":2.8}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, I see.","start":1345.157,"stop":1346.253,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"And, I think it had the same situation that refered to that when it was up here.","start":1346.253,"stop":1349.755,"duration":3.5},{"text":"They did the same thing and your Court pointed that and sees nothing wrong with it.","start":1349.755,"stop":1355.624,"duration":5.87}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Attorney General --","start":1355.624,"stop":1356.154,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":1356.154,"stop":1356.603,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- I think it -- I think it's appropriate for me to say it, as I've now examined the brief for both sides for the Supreme Court of Alabama and the reply brief of the appellant in this case.","start":1356.603,"stop":1369.284,"duration":12.68},{"text":"They are here and in typewritten form.","start":1369.284,"stop":1372.271,"duration":2.99},{"text":"And I -- on my examination you are fully correct that the issue that was posed before the Supreme Court was the issue of construction.","start":1372.271,"stop":1383.965,"duration":11.69},{"text":"And in the -- but this qualification which I do not think is a qualification that the appellants here urged their construction on the ground that a different construction would raise constitutional questions.","start":1383.965,"stop":1401.009,"duration":17.04},{"text":"But the issue of whether or not the Act itself is constitutional was not as an issue put before that Court.","start":1401.009,"stop":1409.557,"duration":8.55},{"text":"You say in this present suit, an answer was filed by the respondent and the sole issue is whether or not the complaint is the labor union or other labor organizations within the meaning of the Solomon Act.","start":1409.557,"stop":1430.588,"duration":21.03},{"text":"And the reply brief by the present appellant takes up questions that were evidently put from the bench in the argument before your Supreme Court and the reply brief does not raise constitutionality but raises the question whether this is an organization that comes within it by virtue of its activities or whether it's the debating or a cultural organization.","start":1430.588,"stop":1442.502,"duration":11.91},{"text":"I think you're wholly correct -- you are wholly correct in my reading of the brief as to the issue that were put before the Supreme Court of Alabama.","start":1442.502,"stop":1448.727,"duration":6.23}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Madison","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":1448.727,"stop":1449.35,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Shadur, and would you respond to that particular phase of the case please?","start":1449.35,"stop":1454.305,"duration":4.96}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor I will.","start":1454.305,"stop":1456.242,"duration":1.94},{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice if it please the Court.","start":1456.242,"stop":1459.232,"duration":2.99},{"text":"I think that a good deal of clarification can be obtained here if we see exactly what the course of this litigation was and why the issues were raised in the places that they were.","start":1459.232,"stop":1471.547,"duration":12.32},{"text":"We start out with the immediately prior to the passage of the Solomon Act with this union which engaged in activities which we will assume for the moment are constitutionally protected.","start":1471.547,"stop":1483.549,"duration":12},{"text":"Now, then, the Solomon Act is passed at that point.","start":1483.549,"stop":1488.141,"duration":4.59},{"text":"In literal terms the Solomon Act applies to the point of union.","start":1488.141,"stop":1493.311,"duration":5.17},{"text":"At that point employees begin to leave it and the union goes to a point where from 250 members you end up with one.","start":1493.311,"stop":1501.785,"duration":8.47},{"text":"We, thereupon, go into the Federal District Court in order to challenge the constitutionality of the Solomon Act.","start":1501.785,"stop":1510.112,"duration":8.33},{"text":"And the Court tells us, \"No.","start":1510.112,"stop":1512,"duration":1.89},{"text":"You can't do that because although perhaps the Solomon Act literally read, is unconstitutional.","start":1512,"stop":1521.891,"duration":9.89},{"text":"We cannot presume that the Alabama courts will so construed it.\"","start":1521.891,"stop":1526.889,"duration":5},{"text":"They then say, \"We will abstain from exercising our jurisdiction until such time as a construction of the statute may be obtained from the Alabama courts.\"","start":1526.889,"stop":1539.056,"duration":12.17},{"text":"Now, then, we go into the state courts.","start":1539.056,"stop":1542.464,"duration":3.41},{"text":"We file the same complaint because we have the same activities.","start":1542.464,"stop":1547.467,"duration":5},{"text":"But because we're doing it in order to obtain a construction so that the constitutional question which is then pending before the District Court, the United States District Court can be raised with the benefit of an authoritative construction of the Act, we then raise it in exactly the manner that Mr. Justice Frankfurter has stated.","start":1547.467,"stop":1569.086,"duration":21.62},{"text":"We put the fact situation before the Court.","start":1569.086,"stop":1572.5,"duration":3.41},{"text":"At that point having put the fact situation before the Court we say, give us a declaratory judgment on this real controversy which exists between this union and the State of Alabama as to whether this statute on these activities can apply to this union.","start":1572.5,"stop":1591.364,"duration":18.86},{"text":"Because if it is applied, it would raise serious constitutional questions.","start":1591.364,"stop":1597.91,"duration":6.55},{"text":"And we stated specifically in the complaint that the purpose of this action, and this is at pages 77 and 78 of the record.","start":1597.91,"stop":1610.54,"duration":12.63},{"text":"This bill for declaration of complainant's rights is brought in part pursuant to the judgment of the United States District Court for the Northern District of Alabama Case Number 7466.","start":1610.54,"stop":1622.026,"duration":11.49},{"text":"And we asserted that the respondents --","start":1622.026,"stop":1625.046,"duration":3.02}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"You've read that though (Inaudible)","start":1625.046,"stop":1626.019,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Pardon?","start":1626.019,"stop":1626.406,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"To obtain (Voice Overlap) --","start":1626.406,"stop":1627.113,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"To obtain construction by the Courts of Alabama which is exactly the reason that we were bringing the complaint.","start":1627.113,"stop":1633.745,"duration":6.63}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Why'd you -- why'd you allege that the Act is unconstitutional in the petitioner, in you complaint?","start":1633.745,"stop":1640.64,"duration":6.9}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Why did we --","start":1640.64,"stop":1641.541,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where'd you allege that?","start":1641.541,"stop":1643.05,"duration":1.51}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"In which complaint, Your Honor?","start":1643.05,"stop":1644.353,"duration":1.3}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In the state court.","start":1644.353,"stop":1645.355,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"In the state court, the only reference to a possible allegation of unconstitutionality is the one that Mr. Justice Brennan referred to in paragraph 10.","start":1645.355,"stop":1657.306,"duration":11.95},{"text":"But we specifically brought this action for construction, for a declaratory judgment because the federal court already had jurisdiction, for purposes of determining the constitutionality.","start":1657.306,"stop":1670.305,"duration":13}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it'd fair to say that you neither sort nor desired a determination of the Alabama court on the issue of constitutionality because you felt that was pending in the federal court and wanted it determined there?","start":1670.305,"stop":1684.303,"duration":14}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":1684.303,"stop":1685.421,"duration":1.12},{"text":"We already had a case pending.","start":1685.421,"stop":1687.158,"duration":1.74},{"text":"The only reason for any Alabama state court proceeding at all is because the judgement of the Alabama state courts on what the statute means, on the construction of the statute, is binding on the federal courts but the court which first had jurisdiction was the Federal District Court, the three-judge court.","start":1687.158,"stop":1707.917,"duration":20.76},{"text":"That was a court in which the constitutional question had been raised and was pending subject only to the obtaining of a construction to see whether our constitutional question may not have been premature but --","start":1707.917,"stop":1722.514,"duration":14.6}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But must the Alabama Supreme Court decide constitutionality on an argumentative implication that the issue before Federal District Court involved constitutionality if they construe it this way?","start":1722.514,"stop":1736.849,"duration":14.34},{"text":"Can Alabama Supreme Court -- were the tedious people, and there's a good deal of respectful autonomy between state courts and federal courts.","start":1736.849,"stop":1747.333,"duration":10.48},{"text":"Why can't the Alabama or the Supreme Court says if you want us to declare these unconstitutional aspects?","start":1747.333,"stop":1754.331,"duration":7}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, the Alabama Supreme Court in the question as presented to us, is confronted with an argument that if it construes the statute so as to cover these activities, serious constitutional problems will be raised.","start":1754.331,"stop":1771.539,"duration":17.21},{"text":"If the Alabama Supreme Court, nevertheless, applies the statute to us, the constitutional question which we have preserved in the three-judge District Court is at point available to us and ripe for determination.","start":1771.539,"stop":1785.389,"duration":13.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But -- but really if you say to the Alabama Supreme Court or to this the constitutional questions are avoided if you construe it one way rather than another, that isn't a necessary and automatic rule that it must construe that way.","start":1785.389,"stop":1801.601,"duration":16.21},{"text":"That is a proper consideration as this Court indicated yesterday.","start":1801.601,"stop":1805.164,"duration":3.56},{"text":"If you please, an important one in construction.","start":1805.164,"stop":1808.839,"duration":3.67},{"text":"But the Alabama Supreme Court for within its power, about which we can say nothing, thought the consideration which were urged to give it one construction rather than another, didn't require that construction.","start":1808.839,"stop":1823.058,"duration":14.22},{"text":"And it came to an end.","start":1823.058,"stop":1824.001,"duration":0.94},{"text":"And it -- in its determination with that.","start":1824.001,"stop":1826.642,"duration":2.64},{"text":"So, that isn't an implication that it would declare that the statute unconstitutional if that issue were pressed before it.","start":1826.642,"stop":1833.736,"duration":7.09}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":1833.736,"stop":1833.784,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That both progress themselves with issues that are pressed before it.","start":1833.784,"stop":1836.854,"duration":3.07}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":1836.854,"stop":1837.401,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Occasionally, rarely and not often wisely they take matters to respondent.","start":1837.401,"stop":1842.149,"duration":4.75},{"text":"But on the whole if one can say we'll only adjudicate the matter that's pressed before us.","start":1842.149,"stop":1847.9,"duration":5.75}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"And that's correct, Your Honor.","start":1847.9,"stop":1849.071,"duration":1.17},{"text":"And the only reason that we were in the state courts was to secure the construction.","start":1849.071,"stop":1853.868,"duration":4.8},{"text":"This is exactly --","start":1853.868,"stop":1854.548,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Were you barred by -- I don't know -- I think about it, needless to say.","start":1854.548,"stop":1858.156,"duration":3.61},{"text":"Were you barred by Alabama, by local law from asking the Court that if you are honest you decide if this Court, you decide the construction question against us then 0.34 whatever it is, then we insist that the statute is unconstitutional.","start":1858.156,"stop":1875.229,"duration":17.07},{"text":"Did you ever do that in the Alabama's Supreme Court?","start":1875.229,"stop":1876.695,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor we did not.","start":1876.695,"stop":1879.519,"duration":2.82}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you place particular significance in the fact that this three-judge proceeding was pending in the District Court?","start":1879.519,"stop":1886.432,"duration":6.91},{"text":"For example, suppose you had not brought any proceeding at all in the federal court until after the proceeding in the Alabama court.","start":1886.432,"stop":1895.163,"duration":8.73}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1895.163,"stop":1895.804,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Would you have been in a better or worst position in your view than you are now?","start":1895.804,"stop":1899.236,"duration":3.43}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I think we would have been in the worst position in that situation.","start":1899.236,"stop":1902.082,"duration":2.85},{"text":"I think, that the pendency of the -- the three-judge court proceeding and the fact that our proceeding into the Alabama courts was in order to comply with the judgment of the three-judge court is a -- is an extremely significant fact in this case because we were directed to go to the Alabama courts, not directed to go there to -- to raise the conditional question --","start":1902.082,"stop":1925.426,"duration":23.34}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you have any feeling that you would be barred under the instructions you had from the District Court from raising the constitutional question in the Alabama court?","start":1925.426,"stop":1939.102,"duration":13.68}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":1939.102,"stop":1939.742,"duration":0.64},{"text":"It was not a question of barring.","start":1939.742,"stop":1941.295,"duration":1.55},{"text":"It was a question of -- of the terms of the direction which the District Court gave us.","start":1941.295,"stop":1946.017,"duration":4.72}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"You comply (Voice Overlap) --","start":1946.017,"stop":1946.109,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"The District Court then told us --","start":1946.109,"stop":1946.717,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":1946.717,"stop":1947.298,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to go, to get a construction of the statue and go to get a construction of the statute we did.","start":1947.298,"stop":1953.632,"duration":6.33},{"text":"And we obtained that construction.","start":1953.632,"stop":1956.095,"duration":2.46},{"text":"Now then --","start":1956.095,"stop":1956.48,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that order in the record a -- when they requested that you go to State?","start":1956.48,"stop":1962.211,"duration":5.73}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":1962.211,"stop":1962.873,"duration":0.66},{"text":"That is in the record.","start":1962.873,"stop":1964.685,"duration":1.81},{"text":"You're having to hear it.","start":1964.685,"stop":1965.471,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1965.471,"stop":1966.38,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll find it.","start":1966.38,"stop":1966.887,"duration":0.51},{"text":"And that's -- in the -- at page 50.","start":1966.887,"stop":1977.74,"duration":10.85},{"text":"Pages 49 and 50.","start":1977.74,"stop":1979.983,"duration":2.24}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":1979.983,"stop":1981.523,"duration":1.54}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Providing that the action is not dismissed but is retained and will remain pending for a reasonable time to permit the exhaustion of such state administrative and judicial remedies as may be available.","start":1981.523,"stop":1991.93,"duration":10.41},{"text":"And immediately following that on page 50, was our emotion filed in the Court in which we advised them that pursuant to the order of the Court entered on November 9, appropriate proceedings will be brought promptly by plaintiffs for construction of the Alabama statute here involved.","start":1991.93,"stop":2008.05,"duration":16.12},{"text":"Now, then, having --","start":2008.05,"stop":2009.521,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Shadur --","start":2009.521,"stop":2009.617,"duration":0.1}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes -- yes, Your Honor.","start":2009.617,"stop":2010.223,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- before you -- you get off of that matter.","start":2010.223,"stop":2013.681,"duration":3.46},{"text":"Can we assume that you and the -- and the Attorney General are -- are in accord, to the effect, that the question of constitutionality was not raised either in your briefs or in your arguments in this proceeding?","start":2013.681,"stop":2034.155,"duration":20.47}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2034.155,"stop":2034.74,"duration":0.59},{"text":"Except in the inferential manner to which Mr. Justice Frankfurter has referred.","start":2034.74,"stop":2041.216,"duration":6.48},{"text":"In the -- in the brief at page 2 in the Alabama Supreme Court, the step, the --","start":2041.216,"stop":2051.634,"duration":10.42}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Was your --","start":2051.634,"stop":2051.982,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- appellants here, in our brief had as Point C.","start":2051.982,"stop":2056.05,"duration":4.07},{"text":"\"If the statute be construed as the community insists, grave issues as to it's constitutionality will be avoided there,\" and it goes on citing the same cases which we refer to here, Wieman against Updegraff.","start":2056.05,"stop":2070.203,"duration":14.15},{"text":"Stating that that is so, that is the avoidance of the constitutional issues because public employees enjoy all the constitutional rights guaranteed by the Due Process Clause.","start":2070.203,"stop":2081.177,"duration":10.97},{"text":"They cannot be removed from public employment in violation of those basic rights.","start":2081.177,"stop":2085.456,"duration":4.28},{"text":"Citing Wieman, we go on to say that the Alabama statute before this Court, if applied to this committee would be incompatible with an exercise of the rights of free speech and free assembly, quoting and citing from Thomas against Collins.","start":2085.456,"stop":2101.816,"duration":16.36},{"text":"And stating, referring specifically to the Federal District Court proceedings in which we had challenged the unconstitutionality, referring to what the Federal District Court had done in directing us to go to the Alabama court and stating that this is why we were before the Alabama court.","start":2101.816,"stop":2121.176,"duration":19.36}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Would you mind stating whether there's anything in what appeared before the Supreme Court of Alabama that would preclude that court today?","start":2121.176,"stop":2133.294,"duration":12.12},{"text":"An issue was before it in agreeing to your argument before this Court that the statute offends the Equal Protection Clause in its exception without at all, even (Inaudible) to adhere to that before that court, that advice which you now claim as a serious body?","start":2133.294,"stop":2161.208,"duration":27.91}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"My recollection, Your Honor, is that the -- the argument which is now appraised as the Equal Protection argument in this Court was not raised in a similar manner to the one that I've just read --","start":2161.208,"stop":2172.194,"duration":10.99}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But the (Voice Overlap) --","start":2172.194,"stop":2172.691,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"-- before the Alabama Supreme Court.","start":2172.691,"stop":2173.668,"duration":0.98}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- argument isn't the -- isn't that -- isn't discrimination?","start":2173.668,"stop":2176.961,"duration":3.29}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":2176.961,"stop":2177.598,"duration":0.64},{"text":"That we -- I say that that argument was not raised in the same term.","start":2177.598,"stop":2180.053,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But -- you -- you urge that strongly here.","start":2180.053,"stop":2182.509,"duration":2.46},{"text":"If you read --","start":2182.509,"stop":2182.682,"duration":0.17}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2182.682,"stop":2183.499,"duration":0.82},{"text":"And I think that it's a substantial point here.","start":2183.499,"stop":2185.294,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But I'm not questioning that.","start":2185.294,"stop":2186.581,"duration":1.29},{"text":"I'm merely suggesting that nothing that the Alabama Supreme Court would bring any (Inaudible) difficulty in its way of deciding, of saying that issue never went before us.","start":2186.581,"stop":2200.122,"duration":13.54},{"text":"We see its substantiality, we yield to it.","start":2200.122,"stop":2203.213,"duration":3.09},{"text":"Is there?","start":2203.213,"stop":2204.951,"duration":1.74}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, the Alabama Supreme Court is on the very issues which are here stated, conscious of the United States Constitution, has held this union and its activities as coming within the Solomon Act.","start":2204.951,"stop":2220.884,"duration":15.93},{"text":"At the time when it knew that we have a pending proceeding which involved and attacked on the constitutionality of the Act if it were applied to our organization and with an argument that raised that problem.","start":2220.884,"stop":2234.524,"duration":13.64},{"text":"Subsequent to that ruling, we came back to the United States District Court and said we have an authoritative construction, which is what you sent us to Alabama for.","start":2234.524,"stop":2244.746,"duration":10.22},{"text":"And having obtained that construction we know say, that this statute as so applied to us, is unconstitutional.","start":2244.746,"stop":2252.813,"duration":8.07}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"But then if we should rule upon the -- on issue as now presented to us and would mean that we might be declaring unconstitutional, an act of the State of Alabama, the Supreme Court of Alabama has not passed on that issue.","start":2252.813,"stop":2267.166,"duration":14.35}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, in -- in passing on the application of the statute the state Supreme Court has reviewed in all aspects, whether this statute can or cannot covered our union.","start":2267.166,"stop":2282.95,"duration":15.78},{"text":"In exactly, the same manner as for example in the Spector cases, which came before this Court, in which there was also the situation of abstention from jurisdiction.","start":2282.95,"stop":2294.26,"duration":11.31},{"text":"And after this Court directed the plaintiffs in that case who were attacking the unconstitutionality of the Connecticut taxing statute, directed those people to go to the state courts of Connecticut.","start":2294.26,"stop":2307.52,"duration":13.26},{"text":"The Supreme Court of Connecticut refused to pass on the -- on the question of the federal constitutional right.","start":2307.52,"stop":2316.092,"duration":8.57},{"text":"It decided what the construction of the statute was, in light of the fact, that there was already a District Court proceeding pending.","start":2316.092,"stop":2323.852,"duration":7.76},{"text":"And armed with that construction, the plaintiffs then came back to the federal courts and came to this Court and this Court decided the merits that that statute as so applied by the Connecticut Court was unconstitutional.","start":2323.852,"stop":2337.074,"duration":13.22}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"This case, the Federal District Court held the case and -- and asked you to go back and exhaust your state remedies.","start":2337.074,"stop":2343.199,"duration":6.13},{"text":"You went back and exhausted them on the -- on the statutory construction but didn't say a thing about the constitutional question that's not been exhausted.","start":2343.199,"stop":2349.4,"duration":6.2},{"text":"Although it's within their jurisdiction to pass on it.","start":2349.4,"stop":2353.788,"duration":4.39}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the exhaustion of the state remedies that was directed by the United States District Court was to secure a construction.","start":2353.788,"stop":2361.341,"duration":7.55},{"text":"Because the thing that the United States District Court hypothesized, Your Honor, was that it was possible that this statute although literally it did not so read, might be applied only to cover an organization in which members belong for the purpose of engaging in collective-bargaining.","start":2361.341,"stop":2380.595,"duration":19.25},{"text":"That issue is no longer in this case.","start":2380.595,"stop":2383.052,"duration":2.46},{"text":"This has -- we have arrived at a conclusive construction and we know have the opportunity to raise this problem.","start":2383.052,"stop":2392.303,"duration":9.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Are there any authoritative finding on the part of your -- your Supreme Court in Alabama, to the effect that this Act as applied to you is constitutional?","start":2392.303,"stop":2407.302,"duration":15}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"An authoritative finding in the Alabama Supreme Court?","start":2407.302,"stop":2409.978,"duration":2.68}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2409.978,"stop":2410.816,"duration":0.84}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"There is no specific statement in the holding with respect to that problem, to my recollection.","start":2410.816,"stop":2417.93,"duration":7.11},{"text":"I might say --","start":2417.93,"stop":2418.158,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"How -- how can we know then that they would find that -- that is the fact?","start":2418.158,"stop":2423.39,"duration":5.23}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"The Attorney General, also argued and much more directly than our argument in the briefs, in the Alabama Supreme Court, that the Solomon Act is valid and is not subject to constitutional objection.","start":2423.39,"stop":2437.385,"duration":14},{"text":"Necessarily, the Alabama Supreme Court's decisions with the arguments that had been placed before it, subsumed the constitutional question even though that they may not have said in so many terms.","start":2437.385,"stop":2449.66,"duration":12.27},{"text":"We find that we can constitutionally do so.","start":2449.66,"stop":2452.704,"duration":3.04},{"text":"They have said, \"Well, we don't think that the activities of these people are strictly such and so.","start":2452.704,"stop":2458.117,"duration":5.41},{"text":"We also find this and therefore this people are a labor union within the meaning of the Solomon Act.\"","start":2458.117,"stop":2464.895,"duration":6.78},{"text":"But having had the arguments presented to them, if they did, both by the Attorney General and by ourselves, they necessarily had to pass that problem in order to find the statute applied.","start":2464.895,"stop":2480.34,"duration":15.45},{"text":"Because if they found the statute applied and as so applied was unconstitutional, then they would either have to say, \"We will construe the statue differently\" or we will say that it would apply, but having so applied it, it is unconstitutional statue.","start":2480.34,"stop":2496.691,"duration":16.35}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, but -- you -- you rely heavily on the question of discrimination here.","start":2496.691,"stop":2503.901,"duration":7.21}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":2503.901,"stop":2505.725,"duration":1.82}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You did not argue that all before the Supreme Court of the State, as I understand.","start":2505.725,"stop":2510.926,"duration":5.2}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, Your Honor.","start":2510.926,"stop":2511.765,"duration":0.84}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, suppose that we didn't take any stock in the rest of your argument, but did rely on that.","start":2511.765,"stop":2519.297,"duration":7.53},{"text":"Would there have been a finding in your Supreme Court based upon on argument, that -- that it was not subject to the objection of discrimination?","start":2519.297,"stop":2533.766,"duration":14.47}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in order to avoid that problem, I am prepared to say that the -- that discrimination argument from our point of view is a constitutional argument in this Court.","start":2533.766,"stop":2545.898,"duration":12.13},{"text":"We would -- if -- if that were a preliminarily question, we would consider that only to the extent that it indicated a violation of due process.","start":2545.898,"stop":2555.58,"duration":9.68},{"text":"So, there is no -- in other words, that the due process argument is enhanced by the exclusions from the statue to the same extent that the basic classification is arbitrary.","start":2555.58,"stop":2568.74,"duration":13.16},{"text":"So, are the exclusions arbitrary and show a due process violation.","start":2568.74,"stop":2570.434,"duration":1.69}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap)","start":2570.434,"stop":2572.703,"duration":2.27},{"text":"They're quite unrelated.","start":2572.703,"stop":2573.623,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I agree, Your Honor.","start":2573.623,"stop":2574.631,"duration":1.01},{"text":"I say that the --","start":2574.631,"stop":2575.112,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean that -- of the statute might be as constitutional -- might be completely void of any difficulty with the Due Process Clause and yet they found on the Equal Protection Clause.","start":2575.112,"stop":2586.34,"duration":11.23}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":2586.34,"stop":2587.135,"duration":0.8},{"text":"I'm saying that this statute --","start":2587.135,"stop":2587.297,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's projecting the Equal Protection Clause out at just the face of due process.","start":2587.297,"stop":2590.921,"duration":3.62}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":2590.921,"stop":2591.436,"duration":0.52},{"text":"I'm not attempting to do so.","start":2591.436,"stop":2592.618,"duration":1.18},{"text":"I say that -- I think that this statute flounders so badly on the Due Process Clause that the Equal Protection problem is not necessary to the case.","start":2592.618,"stop":2601.501,"duration":8.88}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":2601.501,"stop":2601.696,"duration":0.19},{"text":"But you may not agree with your -- the Chief Justice --","start":2601.696,"stop":2603.473,"duration":1.78}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I --","start":2603.473,"stop":2603.587,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- says, we may be more impressed by the exemption.","start":2603.587,"stop":2606.494,"duration":2.91}]},{"speakerName":"Milton I. Shadur","textObjs":[{"text":"I can only hope that you do, Your Honor.","start":2606.494,"stop":2607.749,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"[Laughs] It's a good hope to be probable.","start":2607.749,"stop":2615.977,"duration":8.23}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Apr  29 - 30, 1957","petitioner":"","respondent":"","docket":"423","citation":"353 US 364 (1957)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/353/364","lowerCourt":"","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"May 13, 1957"}